INSERT INTO `monuments_details` (`moun_id`, `m_name`, `title`, `imagepath`, `days`, `location`, `description`, `currency`, `min_price`, `max_price`, `unit`, `timings`, `city`, `entry`, `day closed`, `PIO`, `NRI`, `ticket_status`, `ticket_limit`, `parking_limit`, `parking_limit_for_bikes`) VALUES
(1, 'CHAR MINAR', ' THE CHARM OF CHARMINAR, THE CALM OF HUSSAIN SAGAR LAKE.', 'admin/monument-upload/CHAR MINAR2.jpg', '7', 'Ghansi Bazaar, Hyderabad', '<p> Charminar was built by Sultan Mohammed Quli Qutb Shah in 1591. It is said that this square shaped structure with four pillars and intricate carvings was built in honour of his wife, Bhagmati. However, the actual reason behind building Charminar is still not clear. </p> <p> As per a popular belief, Charminar was built to acknowledge the elimination of the plague which had affected the entire city immensely during that era. It is believed that the Sultan had prayed for the end of this plague with which his people were suffering. Hence, as the plague ended, he built the charminar as a tribute to Allah. The four pillars are also said to be dedicated to the first four caliphs of Islam </p> <p>  There is another legend associated with the Charminar according to which, there is a secret underground tunnel that connects Charminar to the Golconda Fort. It was built for the royal family, to escape in case of any kind of emergencies. However, till date no tunnel could be found. </p>', 'INR', '05', '100', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Andhra Pradesh', 'Paid', 'None', '', '', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(31, 'Chandragiri Fort', '', 'admin/monument-upload/Chandragiri Fort2.jpg', '7', 'Chandragiri, Andhra Pradesh', '<p> Chandragiri was under the rule Vijayanagara empire for about three centuries and came under the control of the Vijayanagarayadava rulers in 1367. It came into prominence during 1560s during the reign of Saluva Narasimha Deva Raya. Later, the most famous Vijayanagara emperor Srikrishna Devaraya, was kept in this fort as a prince, till his coronation at Penukonda.  </p>  <p> It is also said that he met his future queen Chinna Devi at this fort. Chandragiri was the 4th capital of Vijayanagara Empire, Rayas shifted their capital to here when the Golconda sultans attacked Penukonda. In 1646 the fort was annexed to the Golkonda territory and subsequently came under Kingdom of Mysore rule. It went into oblivion from 1792 onward. The Raja Mahal Palace is now an archaeological museum. </p>  <p> The palace is an example of Indo-Sarcen architecture of Vijayanagara period. The crowning towers represents the Hindu architectural elements. The palace was constructed using stone, brick, lime mortar and devoid of timber. Some of important kavyas or epic poems are written in this fort under the patronage of Vijayanagara kings. Inside the fort are eight temples, Raja Mahal, Rani Mahal and other ruined structures </p>', 'INR', '20', '205', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Andhra Pradesh', 'Paid', 'None', '20', '250', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(32, 'CHAND PHIRA GUMBADH', 'A MAUSOLEUM THAT BELONGS TO SYED SHAH MOHAMMAD HUSSEIN IS SITUATED IN THE TOWN OF KUDAPA.', 'admin/monument-upload/CHAND PHIRA GUMBADH2.jpg', '7', 'Kadapa, Andhra Pradesh', '<p> Chand Phira Gumbadh, a mausoleum that belongs to Syed Shah Mohammad Hussein is situated in the town of Kudapa. This mausoleum is hard to miss since it is strategically located right in the centre of the town. The uniqueness of the building lies in its construction and design.  </p> <p> The building is shaped in the form of a square with a large dome built in the centre of the building. Surrounding the building are huge walls to provide protection to the mausoleum. The building is beautifully decorated both from the inside as well as outside. The parapet of the building is covered with platters of arabesque panels.  </p> <p> The mausoleum is a fine example of the architecture during the times of the Nizams since it dates back to their time. It is a curiosity for many tourists because of the tall walls that surround the mausoleum. Many tourists visit the building to get a glimpse of what it is like from the inside. The place is also popular among the local Muslim population. </p>', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Andhra Pradesh', 'Free', 'None', '00', '00', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(38, '', '', 'admin/monument-upload/2.jpg', '7', '', '', 'INR', '', '', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'New Delhi', 'Free', '', '', '', 'Active', '', '', ''),
(39, 'QUTAB SHAHI TOMB', ' A RARE BLEND OF HINDU, PATHAN AND PERSIAN FORMS', 'admin/monument-upload/QUTAB SHAHI TOMB2.jpg', '7', 'Golconda Fort, Hyderabad', '<p> Erected in the memory of the departed kings of Golconda, they are magnificent monuments that have withstood the test of time and natureâ€™s vagaries. They are located one kilometer north of Golconda Fortâ€™s called Banjara Darwaza.  </p> <p> They are imposing marvels of architectural excellence that stand as the reminders of the glory of Golconda kings who are buried at the same spot. Built by the Qutub Shahis, these tombs are considered to be among the oldest historical monuments of Hyderabad. </p> <p>  Today it is maintained well by the Department of Tourism with due focus on heritage preservation and restoration. It is a popular destination in the tourist circuit of Hyderabad and visitors coming to Golconda fort donot miss the tombs, which are marketed as a clubbed destination. </p>', 'INR', '10', '50', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Andhra Pradesh', 'Paid', 'None', '10', '50', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(40, 'CHOWMAHALLA PALACE', 'VINTAGE TOUCH TO NOSTALGIA', 'admin/monument-upload/CHOWMAHALLA PALACE2.jpg', '7', 'Khilwat, Hyderabad', '<p> The history of Hyderabad is so enticing that it feels like reading a wonderful love story and its glorious past is no less than a fairy tale. And the most interesting part of this novel forms the rule of the Nizams, which fills pages of history with legendary contributions of art, architecture and science </p> <p> A testimony to this aspect is seen in the form of the many exquisite monuments scattered all over the city. One such monument that in its striking sumptuousness still shows off the power of time immemorial is the engrossing Chowmahalla Palace. </p> <p>  Presently the palace consists of two courtyards with graceful palaces, the grand Durbar Hall or the Khilwat. Gardens and fountains add to the elegance </p>', 'INR', '80', '200', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Andhra Pradesh', 'Paid', 'Friday', '80', '100', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(41, 'GOLCONDA FORT', ' THE PRINCIPAL CAPITAL OF THE QUTUB SHAHI KINGS', 'admin/monument-upload/GOLCONDA FORT2.jpg', '7', 'Khair Complex, Hyderabad', '<p> Golconda Fort is located in the western part of Hyderabad city and is about 9 km from the Hussain Sagar Lake. The outer fort occupies an area of three square kilometers, which is 4.8 kilometers in length. </p> <p> It was originally known as Mankal, and built on a hilltop in the year 1143. It was originally a mud fort under the reign of Rajah of Warangal. Later it was fortified between 14th and 17th centuries by the Bahmani Sultans and then the ruling Qutub Shahi dynasty. Golconda was the principal capital of the Qutub Shahi kings.  </p> <p>  Golconda still boasts of mounted cannons, four drawbridges, eight gateways, and majestic halls, magazines, stables etc. The outermost enclosure is called Fateh Darwaza meaning Victory gate, after Aurangzebâ€™s army marched successfully through this gate. </p>', 'INR', '05', '100', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Andhra Pradesh', 'Paid', 'None', '50', '100', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(42, 'CHAR MINAR', 'CHARMINAR: A JEWEL OF HYDERABAD', 'admin/monument-upload/CHAR MINAR2.jpg', '7', 'Ghansi Bazaar, Hyderabad', '<p> Charminar was built by Sultan Mohammed Quli Qutb Shah in 1591. It is said that this square shaped structure with four pillars and intricate carvings was built in honour of his wife, Bhagmati. However, the actual reason behind building Charminar is still not clear. </p> <p> As per a popular belief, Charminar was built to acknowledge the elimination of the plague which had affected the entire city immensely during that era. It is believed that the Sultan had prayed for the end of this plague with which his people were suffering. Hence, as the plague ended, he built the charminar as a tribute to Allah. The four pillars are also said to be dedicated to the first four caliphs of Islam </p> <p>  There is another legend associated with the Charminar according to which, there is a secret underground tunnel that connects Charminar to the Golconda Fort. It was built for the royal family, to escape in case of any kind of emergencies. However, till date no tunnel could be found. </p>', 'INR', '05', '100', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Andhra Pradesh', 'Paid', 'None', '05', '100', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(43, 'SALARJUNG MUSEUM', 'AN ART MUSEUM LOCATED AT DAR-UL-SHIFA', 'admin/monument-upload/SALARJUNG MUSEUM2.jpg', '7', 'Darulshifa, Hyderabad', '<p> Situated on the southern banks of Musi River, the Salarjung Museum has a unique distinction as the third largest museum in India and has a worldwide fame for its biggest one-man collections of antiques </p> <p>  It is widely known in India for its prized collections dating back to different civilizations. Nawab Mir Yousuf Ali Khan Salar Jung III, the former Prime Minister of the 7th Nizam of Hyderabad, spent most of his income over a period of thirty-five years to gather such priceless collections, which according to historians was his intense passion. </p> <p>  The renowned museum is now administered by a Board of Trustees which also includes Governor of Telangana as an ex-officio chairperson as per the Salar Jung Museum Act of 1961. </p>', 'INR', '10', '150', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Andhra Pradesh', 'Paid', 'None', '10', '150', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(44, 'DA PARBATIA TEMPLE', 'A PROMINENT HINDU RELIGIOUS SITE', 'admin/monument-upload/DA PARBATIA TEMPLE2.jpg', '7', 'Sonitpur, Assam', '<p> The antiquities found at the Dah Parvatiya are inferred to have been from a temple complex built during the 5th or 6th century, prior to the Bhaskaravarman period. On the basis of the moldings of the torso and its architectural style it is inferred that the terracotta plaques are definitely not later than the 6th century; the altered form of motifs noted in Assam confirms this assessment. </p> <p> This type of architectural feature, particularly in the molds of figurines of the ruins, is seen in North India, in the temples of the Bhumra and Nachha Kuthara which belonged to the Gupta period. Further confirmation of the dating is provided by the carvings of the river Goddesses Ganga and Yamuna, which are also akin to the Greek architecture with striking similarity to the Hellenistic art. The decorative elements of the ruins also have close similarity with those seen in the temples of Orissa. </p> <p>  During the Ahom period, a Shiva temple was built with bricks over the ruins of an ancient Gupta period temple. When the Ahom period temple was destroyed during the Assam Earthquake of 1897, the remains of Gupta period temple were exposed but only in the form of a door frame made of stone. Epigraphic evidence and ancient literature found here, supplemented by the ruins seen scattered around the area, also confirms that in the pre-Ahom period Gupta art extended into the early Medieval period. </p>', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Assam', 'Free', 'None', '00', '00', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(45, 'ANIGARH', 'PRESERVING THE SWEET MEMORY OF YOUNG LOVERS', 'admin/monument-upload/ANIGARH2.jpg', '7', 'Tezpur, Assam', '<p> In the district of Tezpur, Assam, there is a hillock on the bank of the River Brahmaputra called Agnigarh hill. The place is well known for the mythological romance associated with it. According to Hindu mythology, the grandson of Lord Krishna Aniruddha and the daughter of the asura king Banasura, called Usha had fallen in love with each other. </p> <p> Banasura however, did not approve of the match and imprisoned Aniruddha in another place and kept his daughter Usha in seclusion in this place. It was believed that this place had a boundary of fire, which no one could cross without the permission of Banasura, and thus, it was called, Agnigarh or the fort of fire. </p> <p>  The Agnigarh hill area has been developed by the Assam State Government as a beautiful park, adorned by a number of statues, depicting mythological scenes, such as the marriage between Usha and Aniruddha, the abduction of Aniruddha, among others. The place is also well known for the view of the beautiful city of Tezpur as well as the flowing white River Brahmaputra. There are other places to visit nearby, such as the Bamuni hills, Da Parbatia and other places. </p>', 'INR', '00', '50', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Assam', 'Free', 'None', '00', '50', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(46, 'RANG GHAR', 'House of Entertainment', 'admin/monument-upload/RANG GHAR2.jpg', '7', 'Dicial Dhulia Gaon, Assam', '<p> The Rang Ghar in the Assamese language is also called Rong Ghor. The meaning of Rang Ghar means House of Entertainment. It is a building that consists of two-storied, and the architecture of this monument is unique. It is made up of Ahom architecture. It contains a royal origin. </p> <p> People said that the dynasty of Ahom is used for watching different types of sports. It was built in the year 1746. The base of the monuments consists of many entrances, and its roof is very decorative. The monument is entirely made of brick. </p> <p>  The adjoining field, known as Rupohi Pothar, wore a festive look when games like bull-fight, cock-fight, elephant fight, wrestling, etc., were held on different occasions during the Ahom rule. Rang Ghar, besides standing as the royal pavilion, also contributed in spreading the games to different parts of the kingdom and its neighbouring States. </p>', 'INR', '20', '250', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Assam', 'Paid', 'None', '20', '250', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(47, 'SRI SURYA PAHAR', 'SIGNIFICANT BUT RELATIVELY UNKNOWN ARCHAEOLOGICAL SITE IN ASSAM', 'admin/monument-upload/SRI SURYA PAHAR2.jpg', '7', 'Sri Surya Pahar, Guwahati', '<p> Surya Pahar is situated 12 km away from the city Goalpara in Assam. It is established at the banks of the river Brahmaputra. It is an important heritage site of ancient times. The local inhabitants also believed that many hidden mysteries, treasures, and histories are available in Surya Pahar. </p> <p> The spot consists of deities of Hindus, Buddhists, and Jain. All these are scattered and located in just 1 km of an area. It is believed that 99999 Shiva lings are present here for the build-up second Kashi, consisting of 100000 Shiva Lings </p> <p>  According to tradition, the name Sri Suryapahar was derived from the image of Surya Devata It is the only site in the entire North-Eastern region where people and the monarchs of the ages belonging to different faiths had perhaps enjoyed a common platform for worshipping their own Gods and Goddesses and Avatars. </p>', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Assam', 'Paid', 'None', '00', '00', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(48, 'SUKAPHA SAMANNAY KSHETRA', 'THE HONOR OF THE FIRST AHOM KING OF ASSAM', 'admin/monument-upload/SUKAPHA SAMANNAY KSHETRA2.jpg', '7', 'Jorhat, Assam', '<p> Sukapha Samannay Kshetra is built in the honor of the first Ahom king of Assam, Sukapha or Siu-Ka-Pha. He was the founder of the Ahom dynasty, which continued for nearly 600 years. Located in Mohbandha near Jorhat and Derain, it is one of the best historical places in Assam you can visit. </p> <p> Sukapha was a Thai prince who came here crossing the Patkai range. He was the chief person who started uniting the tribal and non-tribal people of the area. Thus, Sukapha Samannay Kshetra was an honor and preserved the remarkable leadership of King Sukapha. Today, excavation has been running here to find any other remains of Sukapha and the Ahom dynasty. </p> <p>  This project has been done in search of the remains of the Ahom dynasty. To reach here, visitors can take tourist cabs, autorickshaws and city buses are also available. The place was built for preserving the leadership of Sukapha </p>', 'INR', '10', '250', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Assam', 'Paid', '', '10', '250', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(49, 'THE GREAT BUDDHA STATUE', 'THE 80-FOOT BUDDHA STATUE', 'admin/monument-upload/THE GREAT BUDDHA STATUE2.jpg', '7', 'Bodh Gaya, Bihar', '<p> The unveiling and consecration of the Great Buddha Statue took place on November 18, 1989. The consecration ceremony was graced with the presence of His Holiness the XIVth Dalai Lama, who blessed the 25-meter statue, the first great Buddha ever built in the history of India.  </p> <p> The Statue is now a symbol of the holy place Bodhgaya, next to Mahabohdi Temple which is a World Heritage site, and enjoys constant visits of pilgrims from all over the world. Among local people, it is nicknamed \"the 80-foot Buddha Statue. </p> <p> Under the slogan \"Spread Buddha rays to the Whole World,\" Daijokyo spent seven years on construction of the Great Buddha Statue, mobilizing 120,000 masons in total. The greatest driving force for this massive project was the pure heart of people, who wish for further expansion of Buddhism from the holy place Bodhgaya, as well as for the realization of world peace. </p>', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Bihar', 'Free', 'None', '', '', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(50, 'KOTESHWARNATH TEMPLE ', 'THE TEMPLE SITE IS IDEAL TO EXPERIENCE POSITIVE ENERGY BY PEOPLE FOR ALL FAITH.', 'admin/monument-upload/KOTESHWARNATH TEMPLE 2.jpg', '7', 'Main, Bihar', '<p> Koteshwarnath Temple is situated in Village Main, Block Belaganj, District Gaya. The temple is situated on the confluence of the river Morhar and Dargha in Gaya, is famous for highly sacred Lord Shiva Temple. Located 90km south of Patna, Koteshwarnath temple is believed to have been build around 8th century AD </p> <p> Koteshwarnath templeâ€™s sanctum is carved in a single piece of red stone and within it is installed a large sized Shivalinga with around 1,008 miniature Shivlingas around 1200 years back.It says that Vanasur Main and DevKund was situated in a deep forest. Usha used to visit the temple to offer prayers during which Lord Shiva appeared & told her to establish a Sahashtra Linga to get her wish full filled.  </p> <p> There is a reference that Sahastra Shiv Ling idol was established at the end of Dwapar Yuga. This Shiv Ling was established by Usha, daughter of King Vanasur of Sonitpur. Itâ€™s a belief that a pilgrimage to this place is powerful enough to full fill all the wishes and desires of the one who comes here. Quite Evidently, Every year In the month of Saawan devotees throng this temple to offer prayers.It says that Vanasur Main & Dev Kund was situated in a deep forest.  </p>', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Bihar', 'Free', 'None', '00', '00', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(51, 'MUNDESHWARI TEMPLE', 'THIS TEMPLE IS LOCATED ON THE SUMMIT OF PIWARA HILL, WITH A HEIGHT OF ABOUT 600 FEET. ', 'admin/monument-upload/MUNDESHWARI TEMPLE2.jpg', '7', 'Ramgarh, Bihar', '<p> The Mundeshwari Devi Temple is a Hindu temple, located at Ramgarh Village, 608 feet on the Mundeshwari Hills of Kaimur plateau near Son River, in the Indian state of Bihar. It is an Archaeological Survey of India protected monument since 1915. .  </p> <p> In the Eastern section of this temple, the grand and ancient idol of the goddess Mundeshwari is the center of the main attraction. The statue of Vishal Nandi on the west side of the main entrance. The uniqueness of this temple is in animal (goat) sacrifice.</p> <p> The mother is in the form of Vaarahi, whose vehicle is Mahish. There are four entrances to the temple, in which one has been closed and one half open. Panchmukhi Shivaling is installed in the central part of this temple.  The color of  the stone This Panchmukhi Shivling has been constructed with a special stone which changes its color along with the position of the sun and stone  </p>', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Bihar', 'Free', 'None', '00', '00', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(52, 'GOLGHAR', ' LARGE GRANARY LOCATED TO THE WEST OF THE GANDHI MAIDAN IN BIHAR', 'admin/monument-upload/GOLGHAR2.jpg', '7', ' Ashok Rajpath Rd', '<p> According to a contemporary inscription at its base, the Golghar in Patna was intended to be just the first of a series of huge grain stores. In the end, however, no others were ever built. The granary was \"part of a general plan for the perpetual prevention of famine in these provinces. A drive to improve the appearance of the structure was begun in 2002.The Golghar or Gol Ghar, is a large granary located to the west of the Gandhi Maidan in Patna, capital of Bihar state. </p> <p> Built in the Stupa architecture, the building has a height of 29 m. It is pillar-less with a wall of thickness of 3.6 m at the base. One can climb to the top of the Golghar via its 145-step spiral stairway. The spiral staircase was designed to facilitate the passage of the workers who loaded and unloaded the grain in the granary, who had to carry grain-bags up one flight, deliver their load through a hole at the top, and descend the other stairs.. </p> <p> Golghar has never been filled to its maximum capacity and there are no plans to do so. Some have claimed that the reason for this is a flaw whereby the doors are designed to open inwards; thus, if it is filled to its maximum capacity, then the doors will not open </p>', 'INR', '25', '100', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Bihar', 'Paid', 'None', '25', '100', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(54, 'SHEH SHAH SURI TOMB', 'THE TOMB OF SHER SHAH SURI IS IN THE SASARAM TOWN OF BIHAR STATE, INDIA. ', 'admin/monument-upload/SHEH SHAH SURI TOMB2.jpg', '7', 'Sasaram, Bihar', '<p> The tomb of Sher Shah Suri is in the Sasaram town of Bihar state, India. The tomb was built in memory of Emperor Sher Shah Suri, a Pathan from Bihar who defeated the Mughal Empire and founded the Suri Empire in northern India. </p> <p> His tomb is an example of Indo Islamic architecture, it was designed by the architect Mir Muhammad Aliwal Khan and built between 1540 and 1545, this red sandstone mausoleum which stands in the middle of an artificial lake, which is nearly square, is known as the second Taj Mahal of India.  </p> <p> The tomb was built during the lifetime of Sher Shah as well as the reign of his son Islam Shah. An inscription dates its completion to 16 August 1545, three months after the death of Sher Shah. </p>', 'INR', '20', '250', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Bihar', 'Paid', 'None', '20', '250', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(55, 'LAXMI VILAS PALACE', 'THE RESIDENCE OF VADODARAâ€™S ROYAL FAMILY', 'admin/monument-upload/LAXMI VILAS PALACE2.jpg', '7', 'Vadodara, Gujarat', '<p> One of the most famous historical places in Gujarat, Laxmi Vilas Palace serves as the residence for Vadodaraâ€™s royal family, Gaekwad. The property has its history dating back to 1890 when it was built by Maharaja Sayaji Rao III. Spanning across an area of 500 acres, the facade itself is intricately designed using the Indo-Saracenic Revival style architecture, let alone the interior that spell grandeur in every inch. </p> <p> A lot many movies have been and are shot in the Darbar Hall of the Laxmi Vilas Palace, as it is available for shoots. The palace is indeed four times bigger than the famed Buckingham Palace, and thus it also is known to be among largest private dwellings in the world. </p> <p> The Lakshmi Vilas Palace in Vadodara, Gujarat, India, was constructed by the Gaekwad family, a prominent Maratha family, who ruled the Baroda State. Major Charles Mant was credited to be the main architect of the palace. </p>', 'INR', '225', '400', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Gujarat', 'Paid', 'None', '225', '400', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(56, '  DWARKADHISH TEMPLE', 'THE TEMPLE DEDICATED TO KRISHNA IN GUJARAT, INDIA ', 'admin/monument-upload/  DWARKADHISH TEMPLE2.jpg', '7', 'Dwarka, Gujarat', '<p> An important Hindu Pilgrimage spot dedicated to Lord Krishna, Dwarkadhish Temple is also known as Jagat Mandir. This is one of the four Char Dhams, and thus it had to be featured in this list of 10 historical places of Gujarat. Supported by 72 pillars, this five-storeyed archeological marvel is said to be as old as 2200 years, as per the findings. </p> <p> The temple is located in Gomti creek, and is always flocked by crowd of pilgrims, especially during the grand celebration of Janmashtami. During this time of the year, the temple and idols are decorated colorfully with garlands, ornaments and different elements. The vibe is full of zest in the locale, making it a must visit.</p> <p> The temple is at an elevation of 12.19 metres  above mean sea-level. It faces west. The temple layout consists of a garbhagriha and an antarala . However, the existing temple is dated to 16th century. </p>', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Gujarat', 'Free', 'None', '00', '00', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(57, 'DWARKADHISH TEMPLE', 'THE TEMPLE DEDICATED TO KRISHNA IN GUJARAT, INDIA ', 'admin/monument-upload/DWARKADHISH TEMPLE2.jpg', '7', 'Dwarka, Gujarat', '<p> An important Hindu Pilgrimage spot dedicated to Lord Krishna, Dwarkadhish Temple is also known as Jagat Mandir. This is one of the four Char Dhams, and thus it had to be featured in this list of 10 historical places of Gujarat. Supported by 72 pillars, this five-storeyed archeological marvel is said to be as old as 2200 years, as per the findings. </p> <p> The temple is located in Gomti creek, and is always flocked by crowd of pilgrims, especially during the grand celebration of Janmashtami. During this time of the year, the temple and idols are decorated colorfully with garlands, ornaments and different elements. The vibe is full of zest in the locale, making it a must visit.</p> <p> The temple is at an elevation of 12.19 metres  above mean sea-level. It faces west. The temple layout consists of a garbhagriha and an antarala . However, the existing temple is dated to 16th century. </p>', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Gujarat', 'Free', 'None', '00', '00', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(58, 'SUN TEMPLE', ' A HINDU TEMPLE DEDICATED TO THE SOLAR DEITY SURYA LOCATED AT MODHERA', 'admin/monument-upload/SUN TEMPLE2.jpg', '7', 'Modhera, Gujarat', '<p> The Sun Temple in Modhera is among the most sought-after historical places in Gujarat, or rather India. This Hindu temple is dedicated to the Sun God, and is located in the embankment of River Pushpavati. In 1026 AD is when Sun Temple was built, back in this time Bhima I of Chalukya Dynasty had the throne. However today, there are no offerings and prayers taking place here, it is primarily a historic site of tourist interest, as maintained by the Archeological Survey of India.. </p> <p> As the inscription is upside down, it evidences the destruction and reconstruction of the cella. Due to the position of the inscription, it is not firmly considered as the date of construction. On the stylistic ground, it is known that the Kunda with its corner shrines was built earlier at the beginning of the 11th century. </p> <p> The inscription is rather considered as the date of destruction by Ghazni instead of the construction. Soon after Bhima had returned to the power. So the temple proper, the miniature and the niche shrines in the tank were built shortly after 1026 CE.  </p>', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Gujarat', 'Free', 'None', '00', '00', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(59, 'Somnath Temple', 'THE IMPORTANT PILGRIMAGE AND TOURIST SPOT OF GUJARAT', 'admin/monument-upload/Somnath Temple2.jpg', '7', 'Veraval, Gujarat', '<p>One of most important monuments of Gujarat, Somnath Temple is said to be the first of Lord Shivaâ€™s twelve Jyotirlinga shrines. As per the findings, the temple has been reconstructed many times, and the most recent change was done in 1951 by adopting Chalukyaâ€™s style of architecture.</p><p>Your tour through the heritage sites of Gujarat would be incomplete if you donâ€™t step foot on this pious landmark. If must be kept in mind that items such as mobile, camera and other electronic gadgets are not allowed inside the temple. You can either leave these items behind in your hotel room or store them in the locker room outside the temple.</p><p>The temple was reconstructed several times in the past after repeated destruction by multiple Muslim invaders and rulers, notably starting from an attack by Mahmud Ghazni in the 11th century</p>', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Gujarat', 'Free', 'None', '00', '00', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(60, ' RANI KI VAV', 'UNESCO WORLD HERITAGE SITE IN GUJARAT, INDIA', 'admin/monument-upload/ RANI KI VAV2.jpg', '7', 'Patan, Gujarat', '<p>Rani Ki Vav was built by Udayamati, in the memory of her husband King Bhimdev 1, in 1063 AD. This massive stepwell was used to take out water from River Saraswati, which has dried today. This is one of the most iconic archeological sites of Gujarat, located in Patan. This is a UNESCO World Heritage Site which displays the rich history and artistry of the state through different sculptures and of course the smart architecture.</p><p>The finest and one of the largest examples of its kind, this stepwell is designed as an inverted temple highlighting the sanctity of water. It is divided into seven levels of stairs with sculptural panels. These panels have more than 500 principal sculptures and over a thousand minor ones that combine religious and symbolic imagery.</p><p>Rani ki vav has been declared a Monument of National Importance and protected by the ASI. It was added to the list of UNESCO World Heritage Sites in India on 22 June 2014</p>', 'INR', '05', '128', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Gujarat', 'Paid', 'None', '05', '128', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(61, 'RANI KI VAV', 'UNESCO WORLD HERITAGE SITE IN GUJARAT, INDIA', 'admin/monument-upload/RANI KI VAV2.jpg', '7', 'Patan, Gujarat', '<p>Rani Ki Vav was built by Udayamati, in the memory of her husband King Bhimdev 1, in 1063 AD. This massive stepwell was used to take out water from River Saraswati, which has dried today. This is one of the most iconic archeological sites of Gujarat, located in Patan. This is a UNESCO World Heritage Site which displays the rich history and artistry of the state through different sculptures and of course the smart architecture.</p><p>The finest and one of the largest examples of its kind, this stepwell is designed as an inverted temple highlighting the sanctity of water. It is divided into seven levels of stairs with sculptural panels. These panels have more than 500 principal sculptures and over a thousand minor ones that combine religious and symbolic imagery.</p><p>Rani ki vav has been declared a Monument of National Importance and protected by the ASI. It was added to the list of UNESCO World Heritage Sites in India on 22 June 2014</p>', 'INR', '05', '128', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Gujarat', 'Paid', 'None', '05', '128', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(62, 'KOS MINAR', 'THE ANCIENT ROYAL ROUTE AND HIGHWA POPULARY KNOWN AS THE GRAND TRUNK ROAD', 'admin/monument-upload/KOS MINAR2.jpg', '7', 'Kos Minar, Haryana', '<p> The Kos minars, erected during reign of Mughal Emperor Jahangir are the earliest known examples of the road milestones in the Indian History. In 1619 AD, Emperor Jahangir ordered Bakir Khan, the Fauzdar of Multan, to erect a minaret at every Kos on the old imperial route. Kos minars are plastered solid bricks structures standing on a square platform. Each minar soars from a tapering octagonal base. </p> <p> Kos Minars were described as a marvel of India by early European travellers such as Sir Thomas Roe and have been labeled as an integral part of India national communication system by Archaeological Survey of India. </p> <p> Kos Minars are solid round pillars, around 30 feet in height, on a masonry platform built with bricks and plastered over with lime. They are not identical. As milestones, they were an important part of communication and travel. </p>', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Haryana', 'Free', 'None', '00', '00', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(63, 'GWALIOR FORT', 'WHERE HISTORY ECHOES THROUGH TIME AND TOWERS', 'admin/monument-upload/GWALIOR FORT2.jpg', '7', 'Gwalior, Madhya Pradesh', '<p>Gwalior Fort, situated in the city of Gwalior, India, is a magnificent fortress that stands as a testament to the regions rich history and architectural grandeur. Perched atop a steep hill called Gopachal, the fort dominates the skyline and offers breathtaking panoramic views of the city below. With its imposing walls, intricate carvings, and ancient temples, Gwalior Fort is a remarkable example of medieval Rajput architecture.</p>  <p>The forts origins can be traced back to the 8th century, although it has been expanded and modified by different rulers over the centuries. The fort witnessed the rule of several dynasties, including the Kachchhapaghatas, Tomaras, Pratiharas, and finally, the Tomars of Gwalior. It was during the reign of the Tomar dynasty that the fort reached its peak of grandeur and was adorned with magnificent palaces, temples, and other architectural marvels.</p>  <p>The fort is divided into two main sections: the lower fort and the upper fort. The lower fort houses beautiful palaces, including the Man Mandir Palace, built by Raja Man Singh Tomar. Known for its exquisite carvings and painted tiles, the palace is a stunning blend of Rajput and Mughal architectural styles. The upper fort is home to the iconic Gujari Mahal, built by Raja Man Singh for his queen, Mrignayani. Today, the Gujari Mahal houses an archaeological museum that showcases a rich collection of artifacts dating back to the 1st century.</p>  <p>Gwalior Fort stands as a symbol of architectural dominance and cultural heritage. Its imposing structure, intricate carvings, and historical significance make it a popular tourist destination and a source of pride for the people of Gwalior. Exploring the forts sprawling complex, visitors can immerse themselves in the rich history, marvel at the craftsmanship of the bygone era, and experience the grandeur of this magnificent stronghold that has stood the test of time.</p>', 'INR', '20', '250', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Madhya Pradesh', 'Free', 'None', '20', '250', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(64, 'DARYA KHANS TOMB AND HATHI MAHAL MANDU', 'DARYA KHANS TOMB AND HATHI MAHAL UNVEILING MANDUS MAJESTIC PAST', 'admin/monument-upload/DARYA KHANS TOMB AND HATHI MAHAL MANDU2.jpg', '7', 'Mandu, Mandav, Madhya Pradesh', '<p>Darya Khans Tomb, located in Mandu, is a striking mausoleum that pays homage to Darya Khan, a nobleman who served under the sultans of the Malwa Sultanate. The tomb, known for its architectural elegance, stands as a remarkable example of Indo-Islamic style.</p>  <p>The structure features a square-shaped base with intricately carved arches and pillars. The main chamber, adorned with ornate jali screens and delicate stone tracery, houses the tomb of Darya Khan. The dome above the chamber is a splendid sight, showcasing a blend of Islamic and Hindu architectural elements, with its lotus-shaped design and intricate patterns.</p>  <p>Hathi Mahal, also known as the Elephant Palace, is an impressive structure within the fort complex of Mandu. It derives its name from the elephant statues adorning its exterior walls. This magnificent palace was constructed during the reign of Ghiyas-ud-din Khilji, the founder of the Khilji dynasty, and served as a residence for the royal ladies of the court.</p>  <p>The architecture of Hathi Mahal showcases a fusion of Islamic and Rajput styles. The palace features intricately carved stone pillars, domes, and balconies. The central courtyard of Hathi Mahal is surrounded by elegant rooms and corridors, offering a glimpse into the luxurious lifestyle of the royals. The palace also houses a grand pavilion with a unique domed roof, providing an elevated view of the surrounding landscape.</p>  <p>Visiting Darya Khans Tomb and Hathi Mahal in Mandu is a journey through history and architectural brilliance. These structures not only reflect the artistic sensibilities of their time but also provide insights into the cultural and historical significance of the region. The intricate carvings, exquisite details, and the overall grandeur of these monuments make them must-visit attractions for history enthusiasts and architecture aficionados alike.</p>', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Madhya Pradesh', 'Free', 'None', '00', '00', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(65, 'JAHAZ MAHAL', 'A MAGNIFICENT ARCHITECTURAL MASTERPIECE IN MADAYA PARADESH', 'admin/monument-upload/JAHAZ MAHAL2.jpg', '7', ' Jahaj Mahal Internal Rd, Madhya Pradesh', '<p>The Jahaz Mahal, also known as the Ship Palace, is a historic structure located in Madaya Paradesh. It is a magnificent architectural marvel that showcases the rich cultural heritage and exquisite craftsmanship of the region. This majestic palace stands as a testament to the grandeur and opulence of the bygone era.</p>  <p>Constructed during the medieval period, Jahaz Mahal is a fascinating blend of Islamic and Rajput architectural styles. It was built as a pleasure resort by the rulers of Madaya Paradesh, offering a retreat from the bustling city life. The palace derives its name from its ship-like appearance, with its elongated structure resembling a floating vessel.</p>  <p>The first paragraph of the palace takes you on a journey back in time, as you step through its intricately carved entrance. The walls of Jahaz Mahal are adorned with beautiful motifs, depicting scenes from ancient epics and legends. The exquisite detailing and precision of the artwork are a true testament to the skilled artisans of that era.</p>  <p>The second paragraph of Jahaz Mahal is a true visual treat for visitors. The palace boasts a stunning courtyard with a central pool, surrounded by arched pavilions and lush gardens. The symmetrical layout of the palace creates a sense of harmony and tranquility. As you wander through the corridors and halls, you can feel the echoes of the past and imagine the grand celebrations and festivities that once took place within these walls.</p>  <p>The third paragraph of Jahaz Mahal unveils its fascinating architectural features. The palace showcases a unique blend of Islamic arches, Rajput domes, and intricate lattice work, creating a mesmerizing interplay of light and shadow. The various levels and terraces provide breathtaking panoramic views of the surrounding landscape, further enhancing the allure of this enchanting structure.</p>  <p>In addition to its architectural splendor, Jahaz Mahal also holds historical significance. It served as a gathering place for poets, artists, and intellectuals, fostering a vibrant cultural atmosphere. The palace witnessed the exchange of ideas, the creation of timeless poetry, and the celebration of art in all its forms.</p>  <p>Today, Jahaz Mahal stands as a revered monument, attracting tourists from around the world. It is not only a symbol of architectural brilliance but also a living testament to the rich history and cultural heritage of Madaya Paradesh. Exploring its halls and courtyards is like stepping into a different world, immersing oneself in the grandeur of a bygone era.</p>  <p>In conclusion, the Jahaz Mahal in Madaya Paradesh is an awe-inspiring architectural masterpiece that captivates visitors with its beauty and historical significance. Its rich heritage and intricate design make it a must-visit destination for those seeking to delve into the glorious past of the region. A visit to this enchanting palace is truly a journey back in time, offering a glimpse into the lives of the people who once inhabited its hallowed halls.</p>', 'INR', '5', '100', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Madhya Pradesh', 'Paid', 'None', '', '', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(66, 'HINDOLA MAHAL', 'A ROYAL ARCHITECTURAL GEM', 'admin/monument-upload/HINDOLA MAHAL2.jpg', '7', 'Sulibardi, Madhya Pradesh', '<p>Hindola Mahal is a magnificent architectural marvel located in Madaya Pradesh, India. It stands proudly as a testament to the rich history and cultural heritage of the region. This resplendent structure has captivated visitors for centuries with its exquisite design and intriguing historical significance.</p>  <p>First constructed during the reign of the Malwa Sultanate in the 15th century, Hindola Mahal served as a grand palace within the royal complex of Mandu. It was built under the patronage of the illustrious ruler, Hoshang Shah, and has since become one of the most iconic landmarks in the region.</p>  <p>The name Hindola Mahal translates to Swinging Palace in English, owing to its unique architectural feature. The palace is characterized by its sloping walls, which create an illusion of a swinging motion, resembling the gentle sway of a swing. This captivating design element is a true testament to the ingenuity and craftsmanship of the artisans of that era.</p>  <p>As you approach Hindola Mahal, you are greeted by its majestic entrance, adorned with intricate carvings and ornate arches. The palace stands tall amidst a vast courtyard, offering a breathtaking view of its grandeur from all angles. The exterior walls are embellished with delicate patterns and motifs, showcasing the mastery of the craftsmen who worked tirelessly to create this architectural masterpiece.</p>  <p>Stepping inside Hindola Mahal, you are transported to a bygone era of opulence and grandeur. The interior is equally impressive, featuring spacious halls and chambers that were once bustling with life. The main hall, with its high ceilings and grand pillars, was likely used for hosting royal receptions and important ceremonies. Its sheer size and architectural grandeur leave visitors awe-struck, providing a glimpse into the lavish lifestyle of the rulers of Mandu.</p>  <p>One cannot help but marvel at the intricate details adorning the walls and ceilings of Hindola Mahal. The stone carvings depict scenes from mythology, floral motifs, and geometric patterns, all meticulously crafted with precision and artistic finesse. The delicate filigree work and latticework add an ethereal charm to the palace, allowing sunlight to filter through and create a mesmerizing play of light and shadow.</p>  <p>From the upper levels of Hindola Mahal, you can enjoy panoramic views of the surrounding landscape, including the picturesque Mandu cityscape and the rolling hills in the distance. It is a sight that evokes a sense of serenity and tranquility, transporting you to a different era.</p>  <p>Exploring Hindola Mahal is like stepping into a living testament of the rich history and architectural brilliance of Madhya Pradesh. It serves as a reminder of the glory days of Mandu and the remarkable legacy left behind by its rulers. Visitors are left in awe of the architectural ingenuity and the intricate craftsmanship that has withstood the test of time.</p>  <p>Hindola Mahal continues to be a source of inspiration and admiration for artists, historians, and visitors alike. Its timeless beauty and historical significance make it a must-visit destination for anyone exploring the cultural heritage of Madhya Pradesh. It stands as a testament to the rich architectural legacy of India and serves as a link between the past and the present, allowing us to glimpse into the grandeur of a bygone era.</p>', 'INR', '5', '100', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Madhya Pradesh', 'Paid', 'None', '5', '100', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(67, 'RANI KAMLAPATI PALACE', 'A GLORIOUS HERITAGE OF INDIA', 'admin/monument-upload/RANI KAMLAPATI PALACE2.jpg', '7', 'Bhopal, Madhya Pradesh', '<p>The Rani Kamlapati Palace is a magnificent historical landmark that exudes grandeur and charm. Nestled in the heart of the vibrant city of Bhopal, India, this architectural marvel stands as a testament to the rich heritage and cultural legacy of the region.</p>  <p>Steeped in history, the Rani Kamlapati Palace was built during the reign of Rani Kamlapati, a prominent queen of the Gond dynasty, in the late 18th century. Its construction reflects a seamless blend of indigenous architectural styles and influences from the Mughal and Rajput traditions, resulting in a captivating fusion of artistic brilliance.</p>  <p>As one approaches the palace, its imposing faÃ§ade commands attention. The palace stands tall, adorned with intricate carvings, delicate jharokhas (balconies), and ornamental domes that grace the skyline. The attention to detail is evident in every nook and cranny, showcasing the unparalleled craftsmanship of the artisans of that era.</p>  <p>Upon stepping inside, visitors are transported to a bygone era of opulence and regality. The interiors of the Rani Kamlapati Palace are nothing short of awe-inspiring. Each room unfolds a story, with its walls adorned with mesmerizing frescoes, depicting scenes from mythological tales and historical events. The delicate motifs and vibrant colors breathe life into the palace, creating a mesmerizing ambiance that leaves visitors spellbound.</p>  <p>The palace is home to a plethora of beautifully manicured gardens and courtyards, providing a tranquil oasis amidst the bustling city. Walking through the well-manicured lawns, one can find respite in the shade of ancient trees and enjoy the gentle melodies of birdsong. The gardens also house charming fountains and reflective pools, adding to the serenity and charm of the surroundings.</p>  <p>Throughout the years, the Rani Kamlapati Palace has witnessed numerous events and played host to dignitaries from around the world. Its majestic halls have echoed with laughter, music, and the clinking of glasses during grand celebrations and royal gatherings. Today, the palace serves as a popular venue for cultural festivals, art exhibitions, and weddings, where its splendor and allure continue to captivate all who visit.</p>  <p>Preserving the historical and architectural significance of the palace, efforts have been made to restore and maintain its original glory. Meticulous restoration work has revived the palace, ensuring that future generations can experience the magnificence of this architectural gem.</p>  <p>The Rani Kamlapati Palace stands as a living testament to the rich heritage and grandeur of the past. It is a cherished landmark that not only showcases the architectural brilliance of a bygone era but also serves as a source of inspiration for generations to come. A visit to this remarkable palace is an immersive journey through time, allowing visitors to appreciate the artistry, culture, and history that define its existence.</p>', 'INR', '20', '250', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Madhya Pradesh', 'Paid', 'None', '20', '250', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(68, 'STAR MONUMENT', 'A STUNNING ARCHITECTURAL BEAUTY, IS BEYOND ADEQUATE DESCRIPTION', 'admin/monument-upload/STAR MONUMENT2.jpg', '7', 'Dinod, Haryana', '<p>The Star Monument in Haryana is a captivating architectural marvel that stands as a symbol of grandeur and cultural significance. Located in the heart of the state, this magnificent structure is a testament to Haryana rich history and architectural excellence. The monument gets its name from its unique star-shaped design, which is a blend of contemporary and traditional elements. It attracts tourists and history enthusiasts from all around the world, offering a glimpse into the rich heritage of Haryana.</p>  <p>The Star Monument is not only visually stunning but also carries deep cultural and historical importance. It serves as a tribute to the glorious past of Haryana, highlighting its contributions to art, culture, and architecture. The monument showcases intricate carvings, vibrant murals, and intricate detailing, representing the skilled craftsmanship of the region. It serves as a reminder of the architectural brilliance of ancient civilizations and their impact on the present-day society.</p>  <p>Visitors to the Star Monument can immerse themselves in the rich heritage of Haryana while exploring its various sections and exhibits. The monument houses a museum that showcases artifacts, sculptures, and paintings, providing an educational and enriching experience. Additionally, the beautifully landscaped gardens surrounding the monument offer a serene environment for visitors to relax and appreciate the beauty of the structure. Whether it exploring the historical significance or simply admiring the architectural splendor, the Star Monument in Haryana offers a memorable experience to all who visit.</p>', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Haryana', 'Free', 'None', '00', '00', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100');
