(69, 'QUTUB KHAN TOMB', 'QUTUB KHAN TOMB IS AN 18TH CENTURY STRUCTURE BUILT IN THE MEMORY OF ADAM KHAN', 'admin/monument-upload/QUTUB KHAN TOMB2.jpg', '7', 'Gurugram, Haryana', '<p>The Qutub Khan Tomb in Haryana stands as an impressive architectural marvel, reflecting the region rich history and cultural heritage. Located in the heart of Haryana, this ancient tomb was built during the medieval period. Named after Qutub Khan, a prominent historical figure associated with the region, the tomb attracts history enthusiasts and tourists alike, offering a glimpse into Haryana glorious past.</p>  <p>The Qutub Khan Tomb showcases a captivating blend of Islamic and local architectural styles. Its exquisite design features intricate motifs, arches, and domes. The walls are adorned with ornate carvings depicting geometric patterns and calligraphic inscriptions, showcasing the skilled craftsmanship of the era. The tomb surroundings include a well-maintained garden that creates a serene ambiance, enhancing the visitors experience as they explore and appreciate the architectural beauty.</p>  <p>Visitors to the Qutub Khan Tomb can delve into the rich history of Haryana by exploring the different sections of the monument. Inside the tomb, one can find the burial chamber of Qutub Khan, while the surrounding area houses smaller tombs and structures associated with noble families from that period. The tomb complex also offers a breathtaking panoramic view of the surrounding landscape, allowing visitors to soak in the historical significance of the location. A visit to the Qutub Khan Tomb is a captivating journey back in time, providing insight into the cultural heritage of Haryana.</p>', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Haryana', 'Free', 'None', '00', '00', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(70, 'SHEIKH CHILLI TOMB', 'SHEIKH CHILLI TOMB IS COMPLEX OF STRUCTURES LOCATED IN THANESAR', 'admin/monument-upload/SHEIKH CHILLI TOMB2.jpg', '7', ' Thanesar, Haryana,', '<p>Sheikh Chilli Tomb in Haryana is a notable historical site that holds great cultural significance. Located in the heart of the region, this tomb is dedicated to Sheikh Chilli, a legendary figure renowned for his wit and humor. The tomb serves as a tribute to his memory and attracts visitors from far and wide who are intrigued by the tales of Sheikh Chilli. With its unique architecture and serene surroundings, Sheikh Chilli Tomb offers a captivating glimpse into the folklore and heritage of Haryana.</p>  <p>The architecture of Sheikh Chilli Tomb reflects a blend of Islamic and local design elements. The structure features intricate patterns, arches, and domes that showcase the skilled craftsmanship of the time. The tomb is surrounded by beautifully landscaped gardens, creating a tranquil ambiance that allows visitors to immerse themselves in the historical aura of the place. As one explores the tomb, they can marvel at the ornate carvings and inscriptions that adorn the walls, providing a glimpse into the rich artistic heritage of the region.</p>  <p>Visiting Sheikh Chilli Tomb offers a unique opportunity to connect with the folklore and legends associated with Sheikh Chilli. According to popular folklore, Sheikh Chilli was a character known for his humorous anecdotes and witty remarks. Many tales and fables have been passed down through generations, highlighting his wit and wisdom. The tomb serves as a pilgrimage site for those seeking blessings and inspiration from the legendary figure. It is not only a historical monument but also a cultural symbol that preserves the legacy of Sheikh Chilli in the hearts and minds of the people of Haryana.</p>', 'INR', '25', '100', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Haryana', 'Paid', 'None', '25', '100', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(71, 'BARSI GATE', 'BARSI GATE IS ONE OF THE FIVE GATES AND THE ONLY SURVIVING GATE THAT SURROUNDED THE WALLED CITY OF HANSI', 'admin/monument-upload/BARSI GATE2.jpg', '7', 'Hansi, Haryana', '<p>Barsi Gate in Haryana holds significant historical and cultural importance. Situated in the heart of the region, this ancient gate is a testament to the architectural brilliance of the bygone era. It served as a prominent entry point to the fortified city and played a vital role in protecting the region from invasions. The name \"Barsi\" translates to \"twelve,\" indicating that the gate was one of the twelve gates that fortified the city. Today, Barsi Gate stands as a reminder of Haryana rich heritage and serves as a popular attraction for history enthusiasts and tourists.</p>  <p>The architecture of Barsi Gate is an exquisite blend of Islamic and local design elements. The gate features intricate carvings, ornamental patterns, and imposing arches, showcasing the skilled craftsmanship of the time. The robust structure of the gate with its towering walls and defensive features reflects the strategic significance it held in protecting the city. Visitors to Barsi Gate can appreciate the intricate detailing on the walls and explore the historical significance of the gate through guided tours or self-exploration.</p>  <p>Barsi Gate not only serves as a historical landmark but also holds cultural importance for the local community. It has witnessed numerous events and celebrations throughout history and continues to be a venue for cultural festivals and gatherings. The gate acts as a symbol of pride for the people of Haryana, connecting them to their roots and preserving their traditions. As visitors pass through Barsi Gate, they are transported back in time, experiencing the grandeur and significance of the historical gateway that has stood the test of time.</p>', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Haryana', 'Free', 'None', '00', '00', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(72, 'RASHTRAPATI NIWAS SHIMLA', 'RASHTRAPATI NIWAS, LOCATED IN SHIMLA, IS A MAGNIFICENT ARCHITECTURAL MASTERPIECE THAT HOLDS GREAT HISTORICAL AND CULTURAL SIGNIFICANCE.', 'admin/monument-upload/RASHTRAPATI NIWAS SHIMLA2.jpg', '7', 'Shimla, Himachal Pradesh ', '<p>Rashtrapati Niwas, located in Shimla, is a magnificent architectural masterpiece that holds great historical and cultural significance. Built during the British colonial era, this iconic structure served as the summer residence of the British viceroys and later became the official retreat of the President of India. Nestled amidst the picturesque hills of Shimla, Rashtrapati Niwas showcases a captivating blend of British colonial and Indian architectural styles, making it a must-visit attraction for history enthusiasts and tourists.</p>  <p>The architecture of Rashtrapati Niwas is truly awe-inspiring. The building features intricate detailing, spacious verandas, and beautiful gardens that offer breathtaking views of the surrounding landscape. The grandeur of the structure, with its majestic halls and elegant interiors, reflects the opulence of the bygone era. The building historical importance is further enhanced by the presence of artifacts, memorabilia, and photographs that provide a glimpse into the colonial history of Shimla and its significance in India  political landscape.</p>  <p>Visitors to Rashtrapati Niwas can explore the well-preserved rooms, including the erstwhile Viceroy chambers, reception halls, and the banquet hall, each adorned with exquisite furnishings and decor. The meticulously manicured gardens surrounding the Niwas offer a serene environment for leisurely walks and provide an ideal setting for events and cultural performances. A visit to Rashtrapati Niwas allows one to immerse themselves in the rich history and experience the grandeur associated with the seat of power during the British Raj and independent India.</p>', 'INR', '30', '65', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Himachal P