(96, 'QILA MUBARAK', 'THE MAJESTIC FORT OF BATHINDA', 'admin/monument-upload/QILA MUBARAK2.jpg', '7', 'Bathinda, Punjab', '<p>Quila Mubarak is a magnificent historic fort situated in the city of Bathinda, Punjab, India. Built in the 18th century, it stands as a testament to the rich cultural heritage and architectural splendor of the region.</p>  <p>The fort is renowned for its architectural grandeur and historical significance. It served as a royal residence for various rulers, including Maharaja Ranjit Singh, the Lion of Punjab. The fort complex comprises several palaces, the most notable being the Darbar Hall and the Qila Androon.</p>  <p>The Darbar Hall, adorned with intricate frescoes and decorative artwork, was once the royal court where the Maharajas held their grand assemblies and entertained guests. The walls and ceilings are adorned with vibrant colors, depicting scenes from mythology, folklore, and royal life, reflecting the artistic finesse of that era.</p>  <p>The Qila Androon, the innermost palace of the fort, is a marvel of architectural craftsmanship. It features a harmonious blend of Mughal, Rajput, and Sikh architectural elements. The palace is intricately designed, with ornate balconies, beautiful arches, and spacious courtyards. It also houses a museum that displays a rich collection of artifacts, weapons, and artworks from the bygone era.</p>  <p>Quila Mubarak holds great historical significance as it witnessed significant events in Punjabs history. It served as a center of power and administration, witnessing the rise and fall of dynasties. The fort also played a role in various historical battles and conflicts.</p>  <p>Today, Quila Mubarak stands as a cherished heritage site and attracts visitors who marvel at its architectural brilliance and delve into the rich history of Punjab. The fort complex offers a glimpse into the opulent lifestyle of the royals and provides insights into Punjabs cultural and artistic traditions.</p>  <p>A visit to Quila Mubarak is a journey back in time, where one can admire the architectural finesse, explore the historical artifacts, and gain a deeper understanding of Punjabs glorious past. It stands as a proud symbol of Punjabs heritage and serves as a reminder of its vibrant cultural legacy.</p>', 'INR', '5', '10', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Punjab', 'Paid', 'Closed on Mondays', '5', '10', 'Active', '', '50', '100'),
