(98, 'SHEESH MAHAL PATIALA', 'THE GLITTERING PALACE OF PATIALA', 'admin/monument-upload/SHEESH MAHAL PATIALA2.jpg', '7', 'District Patiala, Government of Punjab', '<p>The Sheesh Mahal, located in the district of Patiala, Punjab, is a magnificent palace nestled within the Qila Mubarak complex. Built during the 19th century by Maharaja Narinder Singh, it stands as a testament to the architectural brilliance and cultural heritage of Patiala.</p>  <p>The Sheesh Mahal, meaning Palace of Mirrors, derives its name from the intricate mirror work that embellishes its walls, ceilings, and pillars. The mirrors are meticulously arranged, creating dazzling patterns and reflections that add to the grandeur of the palace. This opulent display of glass and mirrors is a visual spectacle that mesmerizes visitors.</p>  <p>Blending elements of Rajasthani and Mughal architectural styles, the Sheesh Mahal showcases a seamless fusion of elegance and artistic finesse. The palaces interiors are adorned with intricate frescoes depicting mythological scenes, royal portraits, and floral motifs. These intricate paintings, executed with precision, exemplify the mastery of the craftsmen of that era.</p>  <p>As visitors explore the Sheesh Mahal, they can wander through its chambers and halls that were once the venue for royal functions and entertainment. Each space exudes a sense of grandeur and provides a glimpse into the extravagant lifestyle of the Patiala royals.</p>  <p>Beyond its aesthetic beauty, the Sheesh Mahal holds historical and cultural significance. It stands as a symbol of Patialas rich heritage and serves as a testament to the artistic achievements of the region. A visit to the Sheesh Mahal offers a unique opportunity to appreciate Punjabs architectural marvels and immerse oneself in the regal splendor of Patialas captivating history.</p>', 'INR', '20', '20', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Punjab', 'Paid', 'None', '20', '20', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(99, 'AMBER FORT', 'MAJESTY ON A HILLTOP', 'admin/monument-upload/AMBER FORT2.jpg', '7', 'Jaipur, Rajasthan', '<p>Amber Fort, also known as Amer Fort, is an awe-inspiring architectural marvel situated in Jaipur, Rajasthan, India. This magnificent fortress, constructed with sandstone and marble, showcases the grandeur and opulence of Rajput architecture.</p>  <p>The fort was built in the 16th century by Raja Man Singh I, a trusted general of Emperor Akbar. Perched on a hilltop, the Amber Fort offers breathtaking panoramic views of the surrounding landscape.</p>  <p>As visitors approach the fort, they are greeted by its imposing walls and fortified gates. The main entrance, known as the Suraj Pol or Sun Gate, leads to the main courtyard.</p>  <p>The interiors of the fort are a visual delight. The Sheesh Mahal, or the Hall of Mirrors, is a dazzling chamber adorned with intricate mirror work, reflecting light and creating a mesmerizing effect. The Sukh Niwas, or the Hall of Pleasure, features a system of water channels that once cooled the summer palace.</p>  <p>The fort is also home to the Diwan-e-Aam, the Hall of Public Audience, where the king would hold court and address the common people. The Diwan-e-Khas, or the Hall of Private Audience, served as a space for private meetings and discussions.</p>  <p>One of the highlights of visiting Amber Fort is the opportunity to ride an elephant up to the entrance gate, a traditional and memorable experience for many visitors.</p>  <p>Amber Fort is not only an architectural masterpiece but also a treasure trove of history and culture. It provides insights into the rich heritage of Rajasthan and the royal lifestyle of the Rajput rulers.</p>  <p>A visit to Amber Fort is like stepping back in time, allowing visitors to immerse themselves in the regal ambiance and experience the splendor of a bygone era. The intricate carvings, exquisite artwork, and stunning vistas make Amber Fort a must-visit destination for history enthusiasts, architecture lovers, and those seeking to unravel the majestic tales of Rajasthan.</p>', 'INR', '25', '550', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Rajasthan', 'Paid', 'None', '25', '550', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
