(101, 'CITY PALACE', 'GRANDEUR IN JAIPUR', 'admin/monument-upload/CITY PALACE2.jpg', '7', 'Kanwar Nagar, Jaipur, Rajasthan', '<p>City Palace, situated in the bustling city of Jaipur, Rajasthan, India, is an exquisite palace complex that stands as a testament to the grandeur and opulence of the Rajput dynasty. Built over several centuries, the palace is a captivating blend of Rajput and Mughal architectural styles.</p>  <p>As visitors enter the City Palace, they are greeted by a series of ornate courtyards, each with its own unique charm and character. The Mubarak Mahal, or the Palace of Welcome, features a stunning blend of Islamic, Rajput, and European architectural elements. Its intricate design and beautiful archways make it a visual delight.</p>  <p>The Chandra Mahal, or Moon Palace, is a seven-story structure that serves as the residence of the current Maharaja of Jaipur. With its delicate frescoes, mirrored ceilings, and exquisite artwork, the Chandra Mahal is a true testament to the craftsmanship and artistic prowess of the artisans of that era.</p>  <p>The Diwan-i-Khas, or Hall of Private Audience, is a grand chamber where the rulers held private meetings and received important guests. Its intricate marble work and ornate decorations create an ambiance of regal elegance.</p>  <p>Within the City Palace complex, there are several other attractions, including the Diwan-i-Aam, or Hall of Public Audience, which was the place where the king would address his subjects. The Pritam Niwas Chowk features four beautifully designed gates, each representing a different season and adorned with unique motifs.</p>  <p>The City Palace also houses a museum that showcases a remarkable collection of artifacts, including royal costumes, weapons, artworks, and ancient manuscripts. This museum provides a fascinating glimpse into the rich history and cultural heritage of Jaipur.</p>  <p>Visiting the City Palace is like stepping into a bygone era, where the grandeur of the Rajput rulers comes to life. The intricate detailing, stunning architecture, and regal ambiance of the palace complex make it a must-visit destination for history enthusiasts, architecture lovers, and those seeking to immerse themselves in the rich cultural heritage of Jaipur.</p>', 'INR', '200', '700', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Rajasthan', 'Free', 'None', '200', '700', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(102, 'CHITTORGARH FORT', 'A CITADEL OF VALOR AND RESILIENCE', 'admin/monument-upload/CHITTORGARH FORT2.jpg', '7', 'Chittorgarh, Rajasthan', '<p>Chittorgarh Fort, situated in the city of Chittorgarh in Rajasthan, India, is a remarkable testament to the valor, honor, and sacrifice of the Rajput warriors. This expansive fortress, perched on a hilltop, encompasses an area of around 700 acres and is one of the largest forts in India.</p>  <p>The fort is known for its formidable walls, stretching over 13 kilometers and rising up to 180 meters in height. These massive walls have witnessed numerous battles and sieges throughout history, with each stone telling tales of bravery and resilience.</p>  <p>Within the fort complex, visitors can explore a multitude of palaces, temples, and towers that showcase the architectural brilliance of the Rajput dynasty. The Rana Kumbha Palace, adorned with intricate carvings and beautiful balconies, stands as a testament to the grandeur of the Rajput rulers.</p>  <p>The iconic Vijay Stambh, or Victory Tower, is a magnificent structure that commemorates the victory of Maharana Kumbha over the combined forces of Malwa and Gujarat. Rising to a height of 37 meters, it offers panoramic views of the surrounding landscape.</p>  <p>The fort is also home to the revered temples of Chittorgarh, including the Meera Temple, Kalika Mata Temple, and Kumbha Shyam Temple, which are not only religious sites but also architectural marvels.</p>  <p>Chittorgarh Fort holds immense historical significance as it has witnessed several sieges, battles, and acts of self-sacrifice by the Rajput warriors. The stories of valor and honor associated with the fort are an integral part of Rajput folklore and have become a source of inspiration for generations.</p>  <p>A visit to Chittorgarh Fort is a journey through time, allowing visitors to immerse themselves in the rich history and heritage of Rajasthan. The imposing fortifications, intricate palaces, and breathtaking vistas offer a glimpse into the glorious past of the Rajput rulers and their unwavering spirit.</p>', 'INR', '15', '200', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Rajasthan', 'Paid', 'None', '15', '200', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(103, 'RANTHAMBORE FORT', 'WHERE HISTORY MEETS WILDLIFE', 'admin/monument-upload/RANTHAMBORE FORT2.jpg', '7', 'Sawai Madhopur, Rajasthan', '<p>Ranthambore Fort, located in the Sawai Madhopur district of Rajasthan, India, is a captivating testament to the rich history and natural splendor of the region. Situated within the bounds of Ranthambore National Park, the fort stands majestically atop a hill, overlooking the picturesque landscape.</p>  <p>Constructed in the 10th century, Ranthambore Fort has witnessed the rise and fall of numerous dynasties, including the Chauhans, Mughals, and Rajputs. It is renowned for its strategic location, serving as a vital stronghold in the bygone era.</p>  <p>The forts architecture displays a magnificent blend of Hindu and Mughal styles, with its grand gateways, impressive ramparts, and intricately carved stone structures. The Ganesha Temple, dedicated to Lord Ganesha, and the Trinetra Ganesh Temple, known for its three-eyed idol, are popular religious sites within the fort.</p>  <p>Aside from its historical significance, Ranthambore Fort offers breathtaking vistas of the surrounding wilderness. The forts elevated position provides visitors with panoramic views of Ranthambore National Park, known for its diverse flora and fauna, including the majestic Royal Bengal tigers.</p>  <p>Exploring Ranthambore Fort allows visitors to delve into the tales of valor, conquest, and royal lineage associated with the region. The forts ruins, ancient palaces, and intricate carvings narrate a vivid story of the past, transporting visitors to a bygone era.</p>  <p>Ranthambore Fort, nestled amidst the enchanting natural beauty of Ranthambore National Park, offers a unique blend of history, wildlife, and scenic landscapes. It stands as a testament to the enduring legacy of the Rajput rulers and is a captivating destination for history enthusiasts, nature lovers, and wildlife enthusiasts.</p>', 'INR', '15', '15', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Rajasthan', 'Paid', 'None', '15', '15', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(104, 'JAISALMER FORT', 'THE GOLDEN JEWEL OF RAJASTHAN', 'admin/monument-upload/JAISALMER FORT2.jpg', '7', 'Jaisalmer, Rajasthan', '<p>Jaisalmer Fort, also known as Sonar Quila or the Golden Fort, is an architectural marvel situated in the city of Jaisalmer, Rajasthan, India. This massive sandstone fortress stands tall in the midst of the vast Thar Desert, casting a golden glow during sunrise and sunset.</p>  <p>Built in the 12th century by Rawal Jaisal, the fort is a remarkable example of Rajput and Islamic architectural styles. Its towering walls, fortified gates, and intricate carvings transport visitors back in time to the era of valor and grandeur.</p>  <p>Within the forts walls, a bustling maze of narrow lanes and alleys awaits exploration. The intricate havelis (mansions) adorned with ornate facades, delicate balconies, and mesmerizing artwork showcase the craftsmanship of bygone eras. The Patwon Ki Haveli, Salim Singh Ki Haveli, and Nathmal Ji Ki Haveli are prominent attractions within the fort complex.</p>  <p>The Jain Temples, dedicated to Jain Tirthankaras, feature exquisite marble carvings and provide a serene and spiritual atmosphere for visitors. The massive Maharajas Palace, or the Raj Mahal, is another noteworthy structure within the fort, offering a glimpse into the opulent lifestyle of the royal families.</p>  <p>One of the highlights of visiting Jaisalmer Fort is the breathtaking panoramic view of the surrounding Thar Desert. From the forts ramparts, visitors can witness the endless expanse of golden sands stretching into the horizon, creating a surreal and mesmerizing spectacle.</p>  <p>The fort also houses several shops, restaurants, and guesthouses, adding to the lively ambiance and making it a vibrant hub for tourists. The bustling narrow streets are filled with colorful shops selling local handicrafts, textiles, jewelry, and traditional Rajasthani artifacts.</p>  <p>Jaisalmer Fort, with its unique blend of architectural brilliance, cultural vibrancy, and enchanting desert backdrop, is a must-visit destination for travelers. It offers an immersive experience into the rich history, traditions, and cultural heritage of Rajasthan, leaving visitors with lasting memories of a truly captivating fortress in the desert.</p>', 'INR', '50', '250', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Rajasthan', 'Paid', 'None', '50', '250', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(105, 'BELGAUM FORT', 'THE FORT ALSO OFFERS BREATHTAKING PANORAMIC VIEWS OF THE SURROUNDING CITYSCAPE, MAKING IT A POPULAR SPOT FOR PHOTOGRAPHY ENTHUSIASTS', 'admin/monument-upload/BELGAUM FORT2.jpg', '7', 'Belgaum, Karnataka', '<p>Belgaum Fort, located in the heart of Belgaum city in Karnataka, is a magnificent historical monument that stands as a testament to the region rich past. Built during the 13th century by the Ratta dynasty, this imposing fort showcases a unique blend of architectural styles influenced by various dynasties that ruled over the region.</p>   <p>The fort is known for its impressive fortifications, with massive stone walls and bastions that enclose a vast area. As you explore the fort, you will come across intricately carved stone arches, ornate balconies, and beautiful temples that add to its grandeur.</p>   <p>Inside the fort, visitors can discover a fascinating mix of structures, including the Kamala Basti, a Jain temple known for its exquisite carvings, and the Safa Masjid, a mosque built during the Bahmani Sultanate period. The fort also offers breathtaking panoramic views of the surrounding cityscape, making it a popular spot for photography enthusiasts.</p>', 'INR', '25', '150', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Karnataka', 'Paid', 'None', '25', '150', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(106, 'BIDAR FORT', 'BIDAR FORT STANDS AS A REMARKABLE EXAMPLE OF MEDIEVAL ISLAMIC ARCHITECTURE, OFFERING VISITORS A GLIMPSE INTO THE REGIONS RICH CULTURAL AND ARCHITECTUR', 'admin/monument-upload/BIDAR FORT2.jpg', '7', ' Bidar, Karnataka', '<p>Bidar Fort, located in the historic city of Bidar in Karnataka, is a magnificent fortress that stands as a testament to the regions glorious past. This architectural marvel was constructed during the Bahmani Sultanate era in the 15th century and later expanded by subsequent dynasties, including the Barid Shahi and the Adil Shahi rulers.</p>  <p>The fort is known for its impressive fortifications, with massive stone walls, bastions, and moats that surround the complex. As you enter the fort, youll be greeted by ornate gateways and intricately carved arches that showcase the architectural finesse of the bygone era.</p>  <p>Inside the fort, visitors can explore a wealth of historical structures, including royal palaces, audience halls, mosques, and gardens. One of the prominent attractions within the fort is the Rangin Mahal, a stunning palace adorned with colorful tile work, intricate carvings, and beautiful frescoes that depict scenes from Persian and Indian mythology.</p>', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Karnataka', 'Free', 'None', '00', '00', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(107, 'KESAVA TEMPLE', 'THE KESHAVA TEMPLE SHOWCASES THE INTRICATE DETAILS AND MASTERY OF THE HOYSALA SCULPTORS', 'admin/monument-upload/KESAVA TEMPLE2.jpg', '7', 'Keshava, Karnataka', '<p>The Keshava Temple, located in Karnataka, is a remarkable architectural gem that stands as a testament to the exquisite craftsmanship of the Hoysala dynasty. This temple, dedicated to Lord Krishna, is known for its intricate carvings, intricate sculptures, and the perfect blend of various architectural styles.</p>  <p>The Keshava Temple showcases the intricate details and mastery of the Hoysala sculptors. The outer walls of the temple are adorned with an array of intricately carved figures depicting gods, goddesses, mythical creatures, and scenes from Hindu epics like the Ramayana and Mahabharata.</p>  <p>Inside the temple, visitors can marvel at the beautifully carved pillars, ceiling panels, and the intricately designed sanctum sanctorum housing the idol of Lord Krishna. The temples architecture follows the traditional Hoysala style, characterized by its star-shaped platform, ornate carvings, and the presence of miniature shrines and decorative motifs.</p>  <p>The Keshava Temple is not only a place of worship but also a treasure trove for art and history enthusiasts, offering a mesmerizing experience of the rich cultural heritage of Karnataka.</p>', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Karnataka', 'Free', 'None', '00', '00', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(108, 'MYSORE PALACE', ' THE PALACE IS KNOWN FOR ITS GRANDEUR AND ARCHITECTURAL SPLENDOR.', 'admin/monument-upload/MYSORE PALACE2.jpg', '7', 'Mysuru, Karnataka', '<p>Mysore Palace, also known as the Amba Vilas Palace, is a magnificent royal residence located in the city of Mysore, Karnataka. This opulent palace is a prime example of Indo-Saracenic architecture and stands as a symbol of the rich cultural heritage of the region.</p>  <p>The palace is known for its grandeur and architectural splendor. With its intricately designed domes, arches, and beautifully carved pillars, Mysore Palace captivates visitors with its stunning beauty. The exterior of the palace is adorned with vibrant colors and intricate artwork, showcasing a fusion of Hindu, Muslim, Rajput, and Gothic architectural elements.</p>  <p>Inside the palace, visitors can explore the elaborately decorated halls, spacious courtyards, and the Durbar Hall, which features a magnificent ceiling adorned with intricate frescoes and crystal chandeliers. The palace also houses a rich collection of artifacts, including royal costumes, jewelry, and paintings, providing a glimpse into the royal history and lifestyle of the Wadiyar dynasty.</p>  <p>Mysore Palace is not only an architectural marvel but also a cultural hub, hosting various cultural events and festivals throughout the year. It stands as a must-visit destination for anyone seeking to immerse themselves in the regal charm and history of Karnataka.</p>', 'INR', '40', '200', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Karnataka', 'Paid', 'None', '40', '200', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(109, 'PATTADAKALLU', 'PATTADAKAL, IS A UNESCO WORLD HERITAGE SITE LOCATED IN THE STATE OF KARNATAKA', 'admin/monument-upload/PATTADAKALLU2.jpg', '7', 'Pattadakal, Karnataka', '<p>Pattadakallu, also known as Pattadakal, is a UNESCO World Heritage Site located in the state of Karnataka, India. It is an ancient temple complex that showcases a magnificent fusion of architectural styles, representing the rich cultural heritage of the Chalukya dynasty.</p>  <p>The temples of Pattadakallu are renowned for their architectural grandeur and intricate carvings. They exhibit a harmonious blend of Dravidian and Nagara architectural styles, with elaborate sculptures and exquisite detailing that depict various mythological stories and scenes from Hindu epics.</p>  <p>Pattadakallu is home to several temples, including the famous Virupaksha Temple, Mallikarjuna Temple, and Papanatha Temple. Each temple is unique in its design and carries its own historical significance. The complex also features intricately carved pillars, mandapas (hallways), and stone sculptures that reflect the artistic brilliance of the Chalukya dynasty.</p>  <p>Visiting Pattadakallu is like stepping back in time, offering visitors a chance to marvel at the architectural splendor and immerse themselves in the rich history and cultural heritage of Karnataka.</p>', 'INR', '40', '600', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Karnataka', 'Free', 'None', '40', '600', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(110, 'BEKAL FORT', 'IT IS ONE OF THE LARGEST AND MOST WELL-PRESERVED FORTS IN KERALA', 'admin/monument-upload/BEKAL FORT2.jpg', '7', 'Bekal, Kerala', '<p>Bekal Fort, located in Kerala, is a captivating historical fortress that stands majestically along the shores of the Arabian Sea. It is one of the largest and most well-preserved forts in Kerala, offering a glimpse into the rich history and architectural legacy of the region.</p>  <p>The fort, built during the 17th century, showcases a unique blend of European and Indian architectural styles. Its massive walls, bastions, and observation towers provide panoramic views of the surrounding landscape and the mesmerizing blue waters of the Arabian Sea.</p>  <p>Inside the fort, visitors can explore various structures, including the ancient underground tunnels, the imposing Hanuman Temple, and the iconic Bekal Fort Beach. The forts strategic location and architectural marvels have also made it a popular filming location for movies in the Malayalam film industry.</p>  <p>With its rich history, scenic beauty, and architectural splendor, Bekal Fort is a must-visit destination for history enthusiasts, nature lovers, and those seeking a serene coastal experience in Kerala.</p>', 'INR', '20', '250', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Kerela', 'Paid', 'None', '20', '250', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(111, 'MATTANCHERRY PALACE', 'IS A HISTORICAL LANDMARK SITUATED IN THE NEIGHBORHOOD OF MATTANCHERRY IN KOCHI, KERALA', 'admin/monument-upload/MATTANCHERRY PALACE2.jpg', '7', 'Kochi, Kerala', ' <p>Mattancherry Palace, also known as the Dutch Palace, is a historical landmark situated in the neighborhood of Mattancherry in Kochi, Kerala. This palace holds significant historical and cultural importance, reflecting the colonial influences and architectural brilliance of the region.</p>  <p>The palace was originally built by the Portuguese in the 16th century and later renovated by the Dutch, hence its name. It is renowned for its traditional Kerala-style architecture, characterized by sloping roofs, wooden carvings, and spacious courtyards. The exteriors of the palace feature intricate murals depicting scenes from the Hindu epics, Ramayana and Mahabharata.</p>  <p>Inside the palace, visitors can explore various sections, including the coronation hall, audience chamber, and royal bedrooms. The palace houses a museum that showcases a rich collection of artifacts, including royal costumes, weapons, antique furniture, and historical documents, providing insights into the royal history of Kerala.</p>  <p>Mattancherry Palace stands as a testament to the regions cultural heritage and offers visitors a chance to immerse themselves in the architectural splendor and historical legacy of Kerala.</p>', 'INR', '02', '50', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Kerela', 'Paid', 'None', '02', '50', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(112, 'KRISHNAPURAM PALACE', 'IS A MAGNIFICENT HISTORICAL PALACE THAT SHOWCASES THE ARCHITECTURAL GRANDEUR AND CULTURAL HERITAGE OF THE REGION', 'admin/monument-upload/KRISHNAPURAM PALACE2.jpg', '6', 'Kayamkulam, Kerala', '<p>Krishnapuram Palace, located in Kerala, is a magnificent historical palace that showcases the architectural grandeur and cultural heritage of the region. Built during the 18th century by the Travancore kingdom, this palace stands as a testament to the rich history and royal legacy of Kerala.</p>  <p>The palace is renowned for its traditional Kerala-style architecture, characterized by sloping roofs, intricately carved wooden walls, and spacious courtyards. It is surrounded by lush greenery and reflects the serenity of its natural surroundings, creating a peaceful ambiance for visitors.</p>  <p>Inside the palace, visitors can marvel at the beautiful mural paintings adorning the walls, which depict various mythological stories and scenes from the epic, Mahabharata. One of the prominent attractions within the palace is the Gajendra Moksha mural, known for its exquisite details and vibrant colors.</p>  <p>Krishnapuram Palace also houses a museum that displays a fascinating collection of artifacts, including ancient sculptures, antique furniture, royal belongings, and historical documents. The palace grounds also feature well-manicured gardens, adding to the charm of the overall experience.</p>', 'INR', '20', '250', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Kerela', 'Paid', 'Monday', '20', '250', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(113, ' HILL PALACE MUSEUM', 'IS A PRESTIGIOUS HERITAGE MUSEUM THAT OFFERS A CAPTIVATING JOURNEY INTO THE ROYAL HISTORY AND CULTURAL HERITAGE OF THE REGION.', 'admin/monument-upload/ HILL PALACE MUSEUM2.jpg', '7', 'Ernakulam, Kerala', '<p>Hill Palace Museum, situated in Kerala, is a prestigious heritage museum that offers a captivating journey into the royal history and cultural heritage of the region. It is located on a picturesque hilltop, surrounded by lush greenery, creating a serene and enchanting atmosphere for visitors.</p>  <p>The museum is housed in the sprawling Hill Palace complex, which was once the royal residence of the Cochin Maharajas. The palace itself is a magnificent architectural marvel, featuring a blend of traditional Kerala and colonial styles. The exteriors are adorned with elegant facades, grand courtyards, and beautifully landscaped gardens.</p>  <p>Inside the Hill Palace Museum, visitors can explore an extensive collection of artifacts that include exquisite furniture, royal regalia, ceremonial swords, paintings, sculptures, and various archaeological findings. The museum also houses a gallery dedicated to numismatics, showcasing a wide range of ancient coins used in the region.</p>  <p>Hill Palace Museum stands as a treasure trove of history and art, allowing visitors to delve into the opulent lifestyle of the Cochin Maharajas and appreciate the rich cultural heritage of Kerala.</p>', 'INR', '20', '250', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Kerela', 'Paid', 'None', '20', '250', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
