(120, 'VELLORE FORT', 'A MAGNIFICENT CITADEL OF HISTORY AND ARCHITECTURE', 'admin/monument-upload/VELLORE FORT2.jpg', '7', 'Vellore, Tamil Nadu', '<p>Vellore Fort is a magnificent fortress situated in Vellore, Tamil Nadu, India. Constructed during the 16th century by the Nayakar chieftains and later fortified by the Vijayanagara Empire, the fort stands as a testament to the architectural brilliance of its time.</p>  <p>The fort, spread across a sprawling area, showcases a blend of Dravidian, Islamic, and European architectural styles, reflecting the influence of various dynasties that ruled the region. Its walls, made of granite blocks, are adorned with intricate carvings and sculptures, adding to its aesthetic appeal.</p>  <p>Within the fort complex, youll find numerous structures of historical significance, including temples, mosques, palaces, and a granary. The Jalakandeswarar Temple, dedicated to Lord Shiva, is a prominent highlight. Its ornate gopuram (gateway tower) and intricately designed pillars captivate visitors.</p>  <p>The fort has witnessed several battles and sieges over the centuries, serving as a stronghold for various rulers. It played a significant role during the Carnatic Wars between the British East India Company and the French East India Company in the 18th century.</p>  <p>Today, Vellore Fort stands as a cherished heritage site and a major tourist attraction. Visitors can explore its vast premises, marvel at the architectural wonders, and delve into the captivating history it holds. The fort also houses a museum that exhibits a wide range of artifacts, including weaponry, coins, sculptures, and paintings, providing a glimpse into the regions past.</p>  <p>With its rich historical legacy, architectural grandeur, and cultural significance, Vellore Fort stands as a proud symbol of Tamil Nadus rich heritage and attracts history enthusiasts, architecture admirers, and curious travelers alike.</p>', 'INR', '5', '5', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Tamil Nadu', 'Paid', 'None', '5', '5', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
(121, 'TAJ MAHAL', 'A SYMBOL OF ETERNAL LOVE AND ARCHITECTURAL SPLENDOR', 'admin/monument-upload/TAJ MAHAL2.jpg', '7', 'Agra, Uttar Pradesh', '<p>Taj Mahal is an iconic mausoleum situated in Agra, Uttar Pradesh, India. It stands as a symbol of eternal love, as it was commissioned by Mughal Emperor Shah Jahan in the memory of his beloved wife, Mumtaz Mahal.</p>  <p>This architectural marvel, built in the 17th century, is crafted entirely from white marble. Its grandeur and intricate detailing make it one of the most breathtaking structures in the world. The Taj Mahal is a fusion of Persian, Islamic, and Indian architectural styles, featuring symmetrical gardens, minarets, a massive dome, and exquisite calligraphy.</p>  <p>As you enter the complex, you are greeted by the charbagh, a Persian-style garden divided into four quadrants. Lush green pathways lined with vibrant flowers lead to the main mausoleum, which houses the tombs of Emperor Shah Jahan and Mumtaz Mahal.</p>  <p>The Taj Mahals exterior is adorned with intricate marble inlays, displaying floral motifs, Quranic inscriptions, and geometric patterns. The interior showcases a breathtaking octagonal chamber with delicate marble lattice screens and precious gemstone inlays.</p>  <p>Visitors can also explore the Taj Museum, which exhibits artifacts related to the construction and history of the monument. The museum provides fascinating insights into the craftsmanship and cultural significance of the Taj Mahal.</p>  <p>Surrounded by lush gardens, fountains, and reflecting pools, the Taj Mahal is particularly enchanting during sunrise and sunset, when its white marble changes hues in the light. The tranquil ambiance and the reflection of the monument in the water create a mesmerizing spectacle.</p>  <p>The Taj Mahal, recognized as a UNESCO World Heritage site, is not just an architectural masterpiece but a symbol of enduring love. It attracts millions of visitors from around the world, who come to marvel at its beauty and immerse themselves in its rich history and romantic aura.</p>', 'INR', '50', '1200', 'Per Person', 'Morning to Night', 'Tamil Nadu', 'Paid', 'Closed on Fridays', '50', '1200', 'Active', '1000', '50', '100'),
