(1, 'CHAR MINAR', 'admin/monument-upload/CHAR MINAR1.jpg', 'INR', '05', '100', 'Per Person', '7', 'Ghansi Bazaar, Hyderabad', 'CHAR MINAR.php', 'One of the most popular historical monuments in Hyderabad, the Charminar was built by Mohammed Quli Qutub Shah in the year 1951. Made of granite and lime mortar, the structure depicts the indo Arabian architecture. It is this monument which has come to symbolize the city of Hyderabad.', 'Andhra Pradesh', 'Active'),
(22, 'Chandragiri Fort', 'admin/monument-upload/Chandragiri Fort1.jpeg', 'INR', '20', '205', 'Per Person', '7', 'Chandragiri, Andhra Pradesh', 'Chandragiri Fort.php', 'Chandragiri Fort is an historical fort, built in the 11th century located at Chandragiri suburb in Tirupati. It is situated in Tirupati district of Andhra Pradesh, India. Although mostly associated with the Vijayanagara Emperors, it was built much earlier in 11th century by the Yadava rulers. In 1460 A.D.', 'Andhra Pradesh', 'Active'),
(25, 'CHAND PHIRA GUMBADH', 'admin/monument-upload/CHAND PHIRA GUMBADH1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', '7', 'Kadapa, Andhra Pradesh', 'CHAND PHIRA GUMBADH.php', 'Chand Phira Gumbadh, a mausoleum that belongs to Syed Shah Mohammad Hussein is situated in the town of Kudapa. This mausoleum is hard to miss since it is strategically located right in the centre of the town', 'Andhra Pradesh', 'Active'),
(37, '', 'admin/monument-upload/1.jpg', 'INR', '', '', 'Per Person', '7', '', '.php', '', 'New Delhi', 'Active'),
(38, 'QUTAB SHAHI TOMB', 'admin/monument-upload/QUTAB SHAHI TOMB1.jpg', 'INR', '10', '50', 'Per Person', '7', 'Golconda Fort, Hyderabad', 'QUTAB SHAHI TOMB.php', 'Qutub Shahi Tombs are constructed in commemoration of the late King of Golconda and has seven toms in the spectacularly laid out gardens of Ibrahim Bagh. Placed just at a distance of a kms from Golconda Fort these are the splendid monuments of architectural dominance.', 'Andhra Pradesh', 'Active'),
(39, 'CHOWMAHALLA PALACE', 'admin/monument-upload/CHOWMAHALLA PALACE1.jpg', 'INR', '80', '200', 'Per Person', '7', 'Khilwat, Hyderabad', 'CHOWMAHALLA PALACE.php', 'Sprawling courtyards, impeccable architecture and unending tourist footfall, the Chowmahalla Palace in Hyderabad promise it all. Though only some parts of the palace are open to the public, yet they are enough to mesmerize the tourists with their sheer charm and grace.', 'Andhra Pradesh', 'Active'),
(40, 'GOLCONDA FORT', 'admin/monument-upload/GOLCONDA FORT1.jpg', 'INR', '05', '100', 'Per Person', '7', 'Khair Complex, Hyderabad', 'GOLCONDA FORT.php', 'The fort that was completed in the 17th century was the stronghold of the legendary Qutub Shahi Empire. One of the best examples of the acoustic systems of the age, this Hyderabad monument still does not fail to surprise the tourists with its extraordinary architecture and style.', 'Andhra Pradesh', 'Active'),
(41, 'CHAR MINAR', 'admin/monument-upload/CHAR MINAR1.jpg', 'INR', '05', '100', 'Per Person', '7', 'Ghansi Bazaar, Hyderabad', 'CHAR MINAR.php', 'One of the most popular historical monuments in Hyderabad, the Charminar was built by Mohammed Quli Qutub Shah in the year 1951. Made of granite and lime mortar, the structure depicts the indo- Arabian architecture. It is this monument which has come to symbolize the city of Hyderabad.', 'Andhra Pradesh', 'Active'),
(42, 'SALARJUNG MUSEUM', 'admin/monument-upload/SALARJUNG MUSEUM1.jpg', 'INR', '10', '150', 'Per Person', '7', 'Darulshifa, Hyderabad', 'SALARJUNG MUSEUM.php', 'The family that built the palace, the Salarjungs were a royal family of Hyderabad and have some of the grandest collections of the antique artefacts to boast of. Being one of the largest museums in the world, the spectacularity of this place cannot be undermined in any regard.', 'Andhra Pradesh', 'Active'),
(43, 'DA PARBATIA TEMPLE', 'admin/monument-upload/DA PARBATIA TEMPLE1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', '7', 'Sonitpur, Assam', 'DA PARBATIA TEMPLE.php', 'The ruins of the door frame of Da Parbatia Temple a few kms. from Tezpur town, is perhaps the finest and oldest specimen of sculptural or iconoclastic art in Assam. The carving has the characteristics of the style of early Gupta School of sculpture. The door jambs having two goddesses, Ganga and Yamuna, standing below with garlands in their hands in artistic pose and elegance are decorated with beautiful ornamental foliage.', 'Assam', 'Active'),
(44, 'ANIGARH', 'admin/monument-upload/ANIGARH1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '50', 'Per Person', '7', 'Tezpur, Assam', 'ANIGARH.php', 'Agnigarh or the rampart, surrounded by fire, is perhaps the most beautiful tourist spots in Tezpur. According to legend, Princess Usha, the only daughter of King Bana, was kept inside the palace which was surrounded by rampart of fire. The present Agnigarh, now only a hillock facing the mighty Brahmaputra, provides the tourist a soul touching panoramic view of both the river and Tezpur town.', 'Assam', 'Active'),
(45, 'RANG GHAR', 'admin/monument-upload/RANG GHAR1.jpg', 'INR', '20', '250', 'Per Person', '7', 'Dicial Dhulia Gaon, Assam', 'RANG GHAR.php', 'It is known as first Ampitheatre or first Pavilion of Asia. It was built by Swargadeo Promotta Singha in the year 1744 A.D. Its shape is octagonal at base. The building has two storeys. At the roof of the structure is shaped like an inverted royal Ahom long boat where there are the projecting heads of two small MAKARAS or JALAHASTIS facing reverse towards north and south. The Rang Ghar was built specially for enjoyment of recreational/sports activities by the royal families and public of the Ahom dynasty.', 'Assam', 'Active'),
(46, 'SRI SURYA PAHAR', 'admin/monument-upload/SRI SURYA PAHAR1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', '7', 'Sri Surya Pahar, Guwahati', 'SRI SURYA PAHAR.php', 'Sri Surya Pahar, also known as Sri Surjya Pahar a site famous for archaeological remains, lies in the Goalpara district. Composed of 7 peaks, spanning over an area of approx. 1400 acres which is located about 13 Kms away from Goalpara town, on the western side. Because of its archaeological importance, the Archeological Survey of India has protected this site of National Importance. It is also a historical site famous for its terracotta, wonderful and exquisite pieces of rock-cut sculpture depicting deities of Hinduism, Buddhism and Jainism. This combination is a rare phenomenon.', 'Assam', 'Active'),
(47, 'SUKAPHA SAMANNAY KSHETRA', 'admin/monument-upload/SUKAPHA SAMANNAY KSHETRA1.jpg', 'INR', '10', '250', 'Per Person', '7', 'Jorhat, Assam', 'SUKAPHA SAMANNAY KSHETRA.php', 'Sukapha was the first Ahom King of Assam. It is located near Mohbandha near Jorhat and Dergaon. This monument was built in memory of King Sukapha. He was the founder of the Ahom dynasty and continues for the next six hundred years. Nowadays, there is an excavation project that is running on this spot.', 'Assam', 'Active'),
(48, 'THE GREAT BUDDHA STATUE', 'admin/monument-upload/THE GREAT BUDDHA STATUE1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', '7', 'Bodh Gaya, Bihar', 'THE GREAT BUDDHA STATUE.php', 'The Great Buddha Statue is one of the largest statues of Gautam Buddha in India, sitting in the meditation pose. Inaugurated in 1989 by the 14th Dalai Lama, this 25 meter high statue took seven years to build with the help of 12,000 workers.', 'Bihar', 'Active'),
(49, 'KOTESHWARNATH TEMPLE ', 'admin/monument-upload/KOTESHWARNATH TEMPLE 1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', '7', 'Main, Bihar', 'KOTESHWARNATH TEMPLE .php', 'Koteshwarnath Temple is situated in Village Main, Block Belaganj, District Gaya. The temple is situated on the confluence of the river Morhar and Dargha in Gaya, is famous for highly sacred Lord Shiva Temple. Located 90km south of Patna, Koteshwarnath temple is believed to have been build around 8th century AD', 'Bihar', 'Active'),
(50, 'MUNDESHWARI TEMPLE', 'admin/monument-upload/MUNDESHWARI TEMPLE1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', '7', 'Ramgarh, Bihar', 'MUNDESHWARI TEMPLE.php', 'The Mundeshwari Devi Temple is a Hindu temple, located at Ramgarh Village, 608 feet on the Mundeshwari Hills of Kaimur plateau near Son River, in the Indian state of Bihar. It is an Archaeological Survey of India protected monument since 1915. . In the Eastern section of this temple, the grand and ancient idol of the goddess Mundeshwari is the center of the main attraction. The statue of Vishal Nandi on the west side of the main entrance. The uniqueness of this temple is in animal (goat) sacrifice.', 'Bihar', 'Active'),
(51, 'GOLGHAR', 'admin/monument-upload/GOLGHAR1.jpg', 'INR', '25', '100', 'Per Person', '7', ' Ashok Rajpath Rd', 'GOLGHAR.php', 'According to a contemporary inscription at its base, the Golghar in Patna was intended to be just the first of a series of huge grain stores. In the end, however, no others were ever built. The granary was \"part of a general plan for the perpetual prevention of famine in these provinces. A drive to improve the appearance of the structure was begun in 2002.The Golghar or Gol Ghar, is a large granary located to the west of the Gandhi Maidan in Patna, capital of Bihar state.', 'Bihar', 'Active'),
(54, 'SHEH SHAH SURI TOMB', 'admin/monument-upload/SHEH SHAH SURI TOMB1.jpg', 'INR', '20', '250', 'Per Person', '7', 'Sasaram, Bihar', 'SHEH SHAH SURI TOMB.php', 'One of the most famous historical places in Gujarat, Laxmi Vilas Palace serves as the residence for Vadodaraâ€™s royal family, Gaekwad. The property has its history dating back to 1890 when it was built by Maharaja Sayaji Rao III. Spanning across an area of 500 acres, the facade itself is intricately designed using the Indo Saracenic Revival style architecture, let alone the interior that spell grandeur in every inch', 'Bihar', 'Active'),
(55, 'LAXMI VILAS PALACE', 'admin/monument-upload/LAXMI VILAS PALACE1.jpg', 'INR', '225', '400', 'Per Person', '7', 'Vadodara, Gujarat', 'LAXMI VILAS PALACE.php', 'The Mundeshwari Devi Temple is a Hindu temple, located at Ramgarh Village, 608 feet on the Mundeshwari Hills of Kaimur plateau near Son River, in the Indian state of Bihar. It is an Archaeological Survey of India protected monument since 1915.  In the Eastern section of this temple, the grand and ancient idol of the goddess Mundeshwari is the center of the main attraction. The statue of Vishal Nandi on the west side of the main entrance. The uniqueness of this temple is in animal sacrifice.', 'Gujarat', 'Active'),
(56, '  DWARKADHISH TEMPLE', 'admin/monument-upload/  DWARKADHISH TEMPLE1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', '7', 'Dwarka, Gujarat', '  DWARKADHISH TEMPLE.php', 'An important Hindu Pilgrimage spot dedicated to Lord Krishna, Dwarkadhish Temple is also known as Jagat Mandir. This is one of the four Char Dhams, and thus it had to be featured in this list of 10 historical places of Gujarat. Supported by 72 pillars, this five-storeyed archeological marvel is said to be as old as 2200 years, as per the findings.', 'Gujarat', 'Active'),
(57, 'DWARKADHISH TEMPLE', 'admin/monument-upload/DWARKADHISH TEMPLE1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', '7', 'Dwarka, Gujarat', 'DWARKADHISH TEMPLE.php', 'An important Hindu Pilgrimage spot dedicated to Lord Krishna, Dwarkadhish Temple is also known as Jagat Mandir. This is one of the four Char Dhams, and thus it had to be featured in this list of 10 historical places of Gujarat. Supported by 72 pillars, this five-storeyed archeological marvel is said to be as old as 2200 years, as per the findings', 'Gujarat', 'Active'),
(58, 'SUN TEMPLE', 'admin/monument-upload/SUN TEMPLE1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', '7', 'Modhera, Gujarat', 'SUN TEMPLE.php', 'The Sun Temple in Modhera is among the most sought-after historical places in Gujarat, or rather India. This Hindu temple is dedicated to the Sun God, and is located in the embankment of River Pushpavati. In 1026 AD is when Sun Temple was built, back in this time Bhima I of Chalukya Dynasty had the throne. However today, there are no offerings and prayers taking place here, it is primarily a historic site of tourist interest, as maintained by the Archeological Survey of India', 'Gujarat', 'Active'),
(59, 'Somnath Temple', 'admin/monument-upload/Somnath Temple1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', '7', 'Veraval, Gujarat', 'Somnath Temple.php', 'One of most important monuments of Gujarat, Somnath Temple is said to be the first of Lord Shivaâ€™s twelve Jyotirlinga shrines. As per the findings, the temple has been reconstructed many times, and the most recent change was done in 1951 by adopting Chalukyaâ€™s style of architecture.', 'Gujarat', 'Active'),
(60, ' RANI KI VAV', 'admin/monument-upload/ RANI KI VAV1.jpg', 'INR', '05', '128', 'Per Person', '7', 'Patan, Gujarat', ' RANI KI VAV.php', 'Rani Ki Vav was built by Udayamati, in the memory of her husband King Bhimdev 1, in 1063 AD. This massive stepwell was used to take out water from River Saraswati, which has dried today. This is one of the most iconic archeological sites of Gujarat, located in Patan. This is a UNESCO World Heritage Site which displays the rich history and artistry of the state through different sculptures and of course the smart architecture.', 'Gujarat', 'Active'),
(61, 'RANI KI VAV', 'admin/monument-upload/RANI KI VAV1.jpg', 'INR', '05', '128', 'Per Person', '7', 'Patan, Gujarat', 'RANI KI VAV.php', 'Rani Ki Vav was built by Udayamati, in the memory of her husband King Bhimdev 1, in 1063 AD. This massive stepwell was used to take out water from River Saraswati, which has dried today. This is one of the most iconic archeological sites of Gujarat, located in Patan. This is a UNESCO World Heritage Site which displays the rich history and artistry of the state through different sculptures and of course the smart architecture.', 'Gujarat', 'Active'),
(62, 'KOS MINAR', 'admin/monument-upload/KOS MINAR1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', '7', 'Kos Minar, Haryana', 'KOS MINAR.php', 'The Kos minars, erected during reign of Mughal Emperor Jahangir are the earliest known examples of the road milestones in the Indian History. In 1619 AD, Emperor Jahangir ordered Bakir Khan, the Fauzdar of Multan, to erect a minaret at every Kos on the old imperial route. Kos-minars are plastered solid bricks structures standing on a square platform. Each minar soars from a tapering octagonal base.', 'Haryana', 'Active'),
(63, 'GWALIOR FORT', 'admin/monument-upload/GWALIOR FORT1.jpg', 'INR', '20', '250', 'Per Person', '7', 'Gwalior, Madhya Pradesh', 'GWALIOR FORT.php', 'Gwalior Fort, located in Gwalior, India, is a historic fortress known for its architectural grandeur and strategic significance. Perched atop a steep hill, it boasts stunning views of the city below. With its imposing walls, intricate carvings, and ancient temples, the fort is a testament to the regions rich history.', 'Madhya Pradesh', 'Active'),
(64, 'DARYA KHANS TOMB AND HATHI MAHAL MANDU', 'admin/monument-upload/DARYA KHANS TOMB AND HATHI MAHAL MANDU1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', '7', 'Mandu, Mandav, Madhya Pradesh', 'DARYA KHANS TOMB AND HATHI MAHAL MANDU.php', 'Darya Khans Tomb and Hathi Mahal in Mandu, India, are notable architectural landmarks. Darya Khans Tomb is an exquisite mausoleum built in the 15th century, showcasing intricate stone carvings. Hathi Mahal, also known as the Elephant Palace, is a captivating structure adorned with elephant-shaped brackets and ornate detailing, reflecting Mandus historical charm.', 'Madhya Pradesh', 'Active'),
(65, 'JAHAZ MAHAL', 'admin/monument-upload/JAHAZ MAHAL1.jpg', 'INR', '5', '100', 'Per Person', '7', ' Jahaj Mahal Internal Rd, Madhya Pradesh', 'JAHAZ MAHAL.php', 'Jahaz Mahal, is a historic structure located in Mandu, Madhya Pradesh, India. Built during the 15th century, it resembles a ship floating in a vast water body. This architectural marvel served as a harem and pleasure palace, showcasing intricate details and offering panoramic views of the surrounding landscape.', 'Madhya Pradesh', 'Active'),
(66, 'HINDOLA MAHAL', 'admin/monument-upload/HINDOLA MAHAL1.jpg', 'INR', '5', '100', 'Per Person', '7', 'Sulibardi, Madhya Pradesh', 'HINDOLA MAHAL.php', 'Hindola Mahal, is a magnificent architectural marvel with sloping walls that create an illusion of swinging motion. Built during the 15th century, it showcases intricate carvings, grand halls, and breathtaking views, representing the rich history and architectural brilliance of the region.', 'Madhya Pradesh', 'Active'),
(67, 'RANI KAMLAPATI PALACE', 'admin/monument-upload/RANI KAMLAPATI PALACE1.jpg', 'INR', '20', '250', 'Per Person', '7', 'Bhopal, Madhya Pradesh', 'RANI KAMLAPATI PALACE.php', 'Rani Kamlapati Palace is a historical palace located in Madhya Pradesh, India. It stands as a symbol of regal elegance and architectural splendor. Built during the medieval period, it showcases exquisite craftsmanship and intricate designs, attracting visitors with its rich history and captivating beauty.', 'Madhya Pradesh', 'Active'),
(68, 'STAR MONUMENT', 'admin/monument-upload/STAR MONUMENT1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', '7', 'Dinod, Haryana', 'STAR MONUMENT.php', 'The Star Monument in Haryana is a captivating architectural marvel that stands as a symbol of grandeur and cultural significance. Located in the heart of the state, this magnificent structure is a testament to Haryana rich history and architectural excellence. The monument gets its name from its unique star-shaped design, which is a blend of contemporary and traditional elements. It attracts tourists and history enthusiasts from all around the world, offering a glimpse into the rich heritage of Haryana', 'Haryana', 'Active'),
(69, 'QUTUB KHAN TOMB', 'admin/monument-upload/QUTUB KHAN TOMB1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', '7', 'Gurugram, Haryana', 'QUTUB KHAN TOMB.php', 'The Qutub Khan Tomb in Haryana stands as an impressive architectural marvel, reflecting the region rich history and cultural heritage. Located in the heart of Haryana, this ancient tomb was built during the medieval period. Named after Qutub Khan, a prominent historical figure associated with the region, the tomb attracts history enthusiasts and tourists alike, offering a glimpse into Haryana glorious past.', 'Haryana', 'Active'),
(70, 'SHEIKH CHILLI TOMB', 'admin/monument-upload/SHEIKH CHILLI TOMB1.jpg', 'INR', '25', '100', 'Per Person', '7', ' Thanesar, Haryana,', 'SHEIKH CHILLI TOMB.php', 'Sheikh Chilli Tomb in Haryana is a notable historical site that holds great cultural significance. Located in the heart of the region, this tomb is dedicated to Sheikh Chilli, a legendary figure renowned for his wit and humor. The tomb serves as a tribute to his memory and attracts visitors from far and wide who are intrigued by the tales of Sheikh Chilli. With its unique architecture and serene surroundings, Sheikh Chilli Tomb offers a captivating glimpse into the folklore and heritage of Haryana', 'Haryana', 'Active'),
(71, 'BARSI GATE', 'admin/monument-upload/BARSI GATE1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', '7', 'Hansi, Haryana', 'BARSI GATE.php', 'Barsi Gate in Haryana holds significant historical and cultural importance. Situated in the heart of the region, this ancient gate is a testament to the architectural brilliance of the bygone era. It served as a prominent entry point to the fortified city and played a vital role in protecting the region from invasions. The name \"Barsi\" translates to \"twelve,\" indicating that the gate was one of the twelve gates that fortified the city. Today, Barsi Gate stands as a reminder of Haryana rich heritage and serves as a popular attraction for history enthusiasts and tourists.</', 'Haryana', 'Active'),
(73, 'RASHTRAPATI NIWAS SHIMLA', 'admin/monument-upload/RASHTRAPATI NIWAS SHIMLA1.jpg', 'INR', '30', '65', 'Per Person', '7', 'Shimla, Himachal Pradesh ', 'RASHTRAPATI NIWAS SHIMLA.php', 'Rashtrapati Niwas, located in Shimla, is a magnificent architectural masterpiece that holds great historical and cultural significance. Built during the British colonial era, this iconic structure served as the summer residence of the British viceroys and later became the official retreat of the President of India. Nestled amidst the picturesque hills of Shimla, Rashtrapati Niwas showcases a captivating blend of British colonial and Indian architectural styles, making it a must-visit attraction for history enthusiasts and tourists.</', 'Himachal Pradesh', 'Active'),
(74, 'THE GATEWAY OF INDIA', 'admin/monument-upload/THE GATEWAY OF INDIA1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', '7', 'Apollo Bandar, Colaba, Mumbai', 'THE GATEWAY OF INDIA.php', 'Mumbais iconic waterfront monument. Symbolizing the citys grandeur and historical significance, it stands tall by the Arabian Sea. A fusion of architectural styles, it reflects Indias colonial past. A must-visit landmark, showcasing Mumbais cultural heritage and offering stunning views of the harbor.', 'Maharashtra', 'Active'),
(75, 'AJANTA AND ELLORA CAVES', 'admin/monument-upload/AJANTA AND ELLORA CAVES1.jpg', 'INR', '10', '250', 'Per Person', '7', 'Ajanta, Aurangabad district, Maharashtra', 'AJANTA AND ELLORA CAVES.php', 'Ajanta and Ellora Caves Ancient rock-cut cave complexes in Maharashtra, India. Ajanta showcases exquisite Buddhist paintings and sculptures, while Ellora boasts a mix of Buddhist, Hindu, and Jain artworks. These UNESCO World Heritage Sites are a testament to Indias rich artistic and religious heritage, captivating visitors with their architectural marvels.', 'Maharashtra', 'Active'),
(76, 'HADIMBA DEVI TEMPLE', 'admin/monument-upload/HADIMBA DEVI TEMPLE1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', '7', 'Manali, Himachal Pradesh', 'HADIMBA DEVI TEMPLE.php', 'Hadimba Devi temple is also known as Dhungari temple or Hidimba Temple and is in the hills of Manali. It is a cave temple dedicated to Hadimba Devi, a figure in the Indian epic Mahabharat. People worship Hadimba as a deity in the form of a huge rock protruding out of the ground. The temple is surrounded by Cedar forest and the place is called as Dhungiri Van Vihar. Outside the temple there is a small part of Mahabharat written and displayed for the public which tells the story of the Pandyas staying in Himachal while they were in exile.', 'Himachal Pradesh', 'Active'),
(77, 'BIBI KA MAQBARA', 'admin/monument-upload/BIBI KA MAQBARA1.jpg', 'INR', '25', '300', 'Per Person', '7', 'Aurangabad, Maharashtra', 'BIBI KA MAQBARA.php', 'Bibi Ka Maqbara is a stunning mausoleum in Aurangabad, India. Built in the 17th century, it resembles the Taj Mahal and serves as a tribute to Dilras Banu Begum, wife of Mughal Emperor Aurangzeb. The mausoleum showcases intricate marble work, elegant minarets, and beautiful gardens, attracting visitors from around the world.', 'Maharashtra', 'Active'),
(78, 'KANGRA FORT ', 'admin/monument-upload/KANGRA FORT 1.jpg', 'INR', '150', '300', 'Per Person', '7', 'Kangra, Himachal Pradesh', 'KANGRA FORT .php', 'The Kangra Fort can be traced back to the Trigarta Kingdom, mentioned in the epic Mahabharata and is one of the largest and oldest forts in India. The history of this fort is very interesting, especially the fact that so many big rulers were unable to conquer this fort. The fort consists of two very old temples; the Laxmi Narayan temple and the Ambika Mata Temple which holds a statue of Rishabnatha.', 'Himachal Pradesh', 'Active'),
(80, 'CHAMPAVATI TEMPLE', 'admin/monument-upload/CHAMPAVATI TEMPLE1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', '7', ' Chamba, Himachal Pradesh', 'CHAMPAVATI TEMPLE.php', 'Champavati Temple is in Chamba district of Himachal Pradesh. It has many temples and other historic palaces. The city is famous for hosting two major local festivals, the Suhi Mata Mela and the Minjar Mela. Both these melas last for several days and is celebrated by the local people in the form of dance and music. The mountains of the Chamba city are also filled with various wall paintings and is famous for its art and craft and textiles. The Champavati Temple was built by the king of Chamba for his daughter. The architecture of the temple fascinates many. The temple is now under the Archaeological Survey of India due to its historical importance.', 'Himachal Pradesh', 'Active'),
(81, 'SINDHUDURG FORT ', 'admin/monument-upload/SINDHUDURG FORT 1.jpg', 'INR', '5', '250', 'Per Person', '7', 'Sindhudurg district, Maharashtra', 'SINDHUDURG FORT .php', 'Sindhudurg Fort is a historic fortress situated in Sindhudurg district, Maharashtra, India. Built in the 17th century by Maratha ruler Chhatrapati Shivaji, it stands on a rocky island off the Malvan coast. This formidable sea fort showcases impressive architecture and served as a strategic defense stronghold. Today, it attracts tourists with its rich history and panoramic coastal views.', 'Maharashtra', 'Active'),
(84, 'CHAND MINAR', 'admin/monument-upload/CHAND MINAR1.jpg', 'INR', '10', '100', 'Per Person', '7', 'Daulatabad, Maharashtra', 'CHAND MINAR.php', 'The Chand Minar is a majestic tower located in Daulatabad, Maharashtra, India. Standing at a height of 70 feet, it was built in the 14th century as a part of the Daulatabad Fort complex. The towers intricate architecture and historical significance make it a captivating attraction for visitors.', 'Maharashtra', 'Active'),
(85, ' BAIJNATH TEMPLE', 'admin/monument-upload/ BAIJNATH TEMPLE1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', '7', 'Baijnath, Himachal Pradesh', ' BAIJNATH TEMPLE.php', 'If you have ever been to Bir on a bus, you would know that Baijnath is the end stop. When you get down at the bus station, the first thing that your eyes notice is the ancient Shiva temple, popularly known as Baijnath temple. This temple was built in 1204 A.D. the architecture of this temple is unique and alluring complimented by the mountain views in the background. The peaceful vicinity of temple offers serenity to mind and soul.', 'Himachal Pradesh', 'Active'),
(86, 'BAIJNATH TEMPLE', 'admin/monument-upload/BAIJNATH TEMPLE1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', '7', 'Baijnath, Himachal Pradesh', 'BAIJNATH TEMPLE.php', 'If you have ever been to Bir on a bus, you would know that Baijnath is the end stop. When you get down at the bus station, the first thing that your eyes notice is the ancient Shiva temple, popularly known as Baijnath temple. This temple was built in 1204 A.D. the architecture of this temple is unique and alluring complimented by the mountain views in the background. The peaceful vicinity of temple offers serenity to mind and soul.', 'Himachal Pradesh', 'Active'),
(87, 'INDIA GATE', 'admin/monument-upload/INDIA GATE1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', '7', 'Rajpath Marg, New Delhi', 'INDIA GATE.php', 'India Gate, located in New Delhi, is a majestic war memorial standing as a tribute to Indian soldiers who sacrificed their lives during World War I and the Afghan Wars. This iconic landmark, surrounded by lush green lawns, serves as a poignant symbol of valor and remembrance, drawing visitors from around the world.', 'New Delhi', 'Active'),
(88, 'QUTUB MINAR', 'admin/monument-upload/QUTUB MINAR1.jpg', 'INR', '30', '500', 'Per Person', '7', 'Mehrauli, New Delhi', 'QUTUB MINAR.php', 'Qutub Minar, located in Delhi, India, is a towering masterpiece of Indo-Islamic architecture. Standing at 73 meters, it showcases intricate carvings and inscriptions from the Quran. Built in the 12th century, it is a UNESCO World Heritage Site and a testament to the rich history and cultural heritage of India.', 'New Delhi', 'Active'),
(89, 'AKSHARDHAM MANDIR', 'admin/monument-upload/AKSHARDHAM MANDIR1.jpg', 'INR', '', '', 'Per Person', '7', 'Pandav Nagar, New Delhi', 'AKSHARDHAM MANDIR.php', 'Akshardham Mandir, located in Delhi, India, is a breathtaking temple complex showcasing exquisite architecture and spiritual grandeur. Built in 2005, it is renowned for its intricate carvings, magnificent sculptures, and captivating light and sound shows. The mandir is a revered spiritual destination and a marvel of craftsmanship.', 'New Delhi', 'Active'),
(90, 'HUMAYUN TOMB', 'admin/monument-upload/HUMAYUN TOMB1.jpg', 'INR', '30', '500', 'Per Person', '7', 'Mathura Road, New Delhi', 'HUMAYUN TOMB.php', 'Humayuns Tomb is a magnificent mausoleum located in Delhi, India. Built in the 16th century, it is an exemplary masterpiece of Mughal architecture. The tomb, surrounded by lush gardens, is a UNESCO World Heritage Site and serves as a tribute to Emperor Humayun, the second Mughal emperor of India.', 'New Delhi', 'Active'),
(91, 'DIWAN-I-AAM', 'admin/monument-upload/DIWAN-I-AAM1.jpg', 'INR', '', '', 'Per Person', '7', 'Opp Lal Qila, Old Delhi', 'DIWAN-I-AAM.php', 'Diwan-i-Aam, located within the Red Fort in Delhi, India, served as the hall of public audience during the Mughal era. This architectural marvel, adorned with intricate designs and beautiful carvings, provided a grand setting for the emperor to address and interact with the common people of the empire.', 'New Delhi', 'Active'),
(92, 'SRI HARMANDIR SAHIB', 'admin/monument-upload/SRI HARMANDIR SAHIB1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', '7', 'Amritsar, Punjab', 'SRI HARMANDIR SAHIB.php', 'Sri Harmandir Sahib, known as the Golden Temple, is a revered Sikh gurdwara in Amritsar, India. This holiest shrine in Sikhism features a magnificent golden structure surrounded by a sacred pool. It draws millions of devotees, offering spiritual solace and showcasing the rich Sikh heritage.', 'Punjab', 'Active'),
(93, 'JALLIANWALA BAGH', 'admin/monument-upload/JALLIANWALA BAGH1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', '7', 'Amritsar, Punjab', 'JALLIANWALA BAGH.php', 'Jallianwala Bagh is a public garden in Amritsar, India, known for the infamous Jallianwala Bagh massacre of 1919. The site holds historical significance as it witnessed the brutal killing of hundreds of unarmed Indians by British troops. Today, it serves as a memorial and reminder of the struggle for Indian independence.', 'Punjab', 'Active'),
(94, 'AKAL TAKHT', 'admin/monument-upload/AKAL TAKHT1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', '7', 'Amritsar, Punjab', 'AKAL TAKHT.php', 'Akal Takht, situated within the Golden Temple Complex in Amritsar, India, is the highest temporal seat of Sikh authority. It serves as a central place for Sikh religious and political deliberations. The Takht represents the Sikh communitys strength, resilience, and commitment to upholding religious principles and social justice.', 'Punjab', 'Active'),
(95, 'SHEESH MAHAL PATIALA', 'admin/monument-upload/SHEESH MAHAL PATIALA1.jpg', 'INR', '20', '20', 'Per Person', '7', 'District Patiala, Government of Punjab', 'SHEESH MAHAL PATIALA.php', 'The Sheesh Mahal was built behind the main Moti Bagh Palace to serve as a pleasure complex.The paintings in two of its well maintained , mirror-worked chambers are of Kangra and Rajasthani qalam, depicting the poetic visions of Keshav, Surdas and Bihari. The Sheesh Mahal now houses a museum, an art gallery, the famed medal gallery and also the North Zone Cultural Centre.', 'Punjab', 'Active'),
(96, 'AMBER FORT', 'admin/monument-upload/AMBER FORT1.jpg', 'INR', '25', '550', 'Per Person', '7', 'Amer, Jaipur, Rajasthan', 'AMBER FORT.php', 'Amber Fort, located in Jaipur, Rajasthan, India, is a magnificent fortress known for its architectural grandeur and historical significance. With its impressive ramparts, stunning palaces, and intricate artwork, the fort offers visitors a glimpse into the rich cultural heritage of the region and stands as a testament to Rajasthans regal history.', 'Rajasthan', 'Active'),
(97, 'CITY PALACE', 'admin/monument-upload/CITY PALACE1.jpg', 'INR', '200', '700', 'Per Person', '7', 'Kanwar Nagar, Jaipur, Rajasthan', 'CITY PALACE.php', 'City Palace, located in the heart of Jaipur, Rajasthan, India, is a magnificent palace complex that showcases the rich heritage and architectural splendor of the region. With its stunning courtyards, grand halls, and intricate detailing, it offers visitors a glimpse into the opulent lifestyle of the royal families of Jaipur.', 'Rajasthan', 'Active'),
(98, 'CHITTORGARH FORT', 'admin/monument-upload/CHITTORGARH FORT1.jpg', 'INR', '15', '200', 'Per Person', '7', 'Chittorgarh, Rajasthan', 'CHITTORGARH FORT.php', 'Chittorgarh Fort, located in Chittorgarh, Rajasthan, India, is a majestic fortress that narrates the tales of valor and sacrifice. With its massive walls, grand palaces, and historic significance, it stands as a symbol of Rajput pride and resilience, offering visitors a glimpse into the rich history of Rajasthan.', 'Rajasthan', 'Active'),
(99, 'RANTHAMBORE FORT', 'admin/monument-upload/RANTHAMBORE FORT1.jpg', 'INR', '15', '15', 'Per Person', '7', 'Sawai Madhopur, Rajasthan', 'RANTHAMBORE FORT.php', 'Ranthambore Fort, situated in the Sawai Madhopur district of Rajasthan, India, is an ancient fortress steeped in history and natural beauty. Located within Ranthambore National Park, it offers panoramic views of the surrounding wildlife sanctuary and is a popular destination for wildlife enthusiasts and history buffs alike.', 'Rajasthan', 'Active'),
(100, 'JAISALMER FORT', 'admin/monument-upload/JAISALMER FORT1.jpg', 'INR', '50', '250', 'Per Person', '7', 'Jaisalmer, Rajasthan', 'JAISALMER FORT.php', 'Jaisalmer Fort, located in the heart of the city of Jaisalmer in Rajasthan, India, is a magnificent sandstone fortress rising from the Thar Desert. Known as the Golden Fort, it is a UNESCO World Heritage Site and boasts intricate architecture, bustling marketplaces, and stunning panoramic views of the surrounding desert landscape.', 'Rajasthan', 'Active'),
(103, 'BELGAUM FORT', 'admin/monument-upload/BELGAUM FORT1.jpg', 'INR', '25', '150', 'Per Person', '7', 'Belgaum, Karnataka', 'BELGAUM FORT.php', 'Belgaum Fort, located in the heart of Belgaum city in Karnataka, is a magnificent historical monument that stands as a testament to the region rich past. Built during the 13th century by the Ratta dynasty, this imposing fort showcases a unique blend of architectural styles influenced by various dynasties that ruled over the region.</', 'Karnataka', 'Active'),
(104, 'BIDAR FORT', 'admin/monument-upload/BIDAR FORT1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', '7', ' Bidar, Karnataka', 'BIDAR FORT.php', 'Bidar Fort, located in the historic city of Bidar in Karnataka, is a magnificent fortress that stands as a testament to the regions glorious past. This architectural marvel was constructed during the Bahmani Sultanate era in the 15th century and later expanded by subsequent dynasties, including the Barid Shahi and the Adil Shahi rulers', 'Karnataka', 'Active'),
(105, 'KESAVA TEMPLE', 'admin/monument-upload/KESAVA TEMPLE1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', '7', 'Keshava, Karnataka', 'KESAVA TEMPLE.php', 'The Keshava Temple, located in Karnataka, is a remarkable architectural gem that stands as a testament to the exquisite craftsmanship of the Hoysala dynasty. This temple, dedicated to Lord Krishna, is known for its intricate carvings, intricate sculptures, and the perfect blend of various architectural styles', 'Karnataka', 'Active'),
(106, 'MYSORE PALACE', 'admin/monument-upload/MYSORE PALACE1.jpg', 'INR', '40', '200', 'Per Person', '7', 'Mysuru, Karnataka', 'MYSORE PALACE.php', 'Mysore Palace, also known as the Amba Vilas Palace, is a magnificent royal residence located in the city of Mysore, Karnataka. This opulent palace is a prime example of Indo-Saracenic architecture and stands as a symbol of the rich cultural heritage of the region', 'Karnataka', 'Active'),
(107, 'PATTADAKALLU', 'admin/monument-upload/PATTADAKALLU1.jpg', 'INR', '40', '600', 'Per Person', '7', 'Pattadakal, Karnataka', 'PATTADAKALLU.php', 'Pattadakallu, also known as Pattadakal, is a UNESCO World Heritage Site located in the state of Karnataka, India. It is an ancient temple complex that showcases a magnificent fusion of architectural styles, representing the rich cultural heritage of the Chalukya dynasty.', 'Karnataka', 'Active'),
(108, 'BEKAL FORT', 'admin/monument-upload/BEKAL FORT1.jpg', 'INR', '20', '250', 'Per Person', '7', 'Bekal, Kerala', 'BEKAL FORT.php', 'Bekal Fort, located in Kerala, is a captivating historical fortress that stands majestically along the shores of the Arabian Sea. It is one of the largest and most well-preserved forts in Kerala, offering a glimpse into the rich history and architectural legacy of the region', 'Kerela', 'Active'),
(109, 'BEKAL FORT', 'admin/monument-upload/BEKAL FORT1.jpg', 'INR', '20', '250', 'Per Person', '7', 'Bekal, Kerala', 'BEKAL FORT.php', 'Bekal Fort, located in Kerala, is a captivating historical fortress that stands majestically along the shores of the Arabian Sea. It is one of the largest and most well-preserved forts in Kerala, offering a glimpse into the rich history and architectural legacy of the region', 'Kerela', 'Active'),
(110, 'MATTANCHERRY PALACE', 'admin/monument-upload/MATTANCHERRY PALACE1.jpg', 'INR', '02', '50', 'Per Person', '7', 'Kochi, Kerala', 'MATTANCHERRY PALACE.php', 'Mattancherry Palace, also known as the Dutch Palace, is a historical landmark situated in the neighborhood of Mattancherry in Kochi, Kerala. This palace holds significant historical and cultural importance, reflecting the colonial influences and architectural brilliance of the region.', 'Kerela', 'Active'),
(111, 'MATTANCHERRY PALACE', 'admin/monument-upload/MATTANCHERRY PALACE1.jpg', 'INR', '02', '50', 'Per Person', '7', 'Kochi, Kerala', 'MATTANCHERRY PALACE.php', 'Mattancherry Palace, also known as the Dutch Palace, is a historical landmark situated in the neighborhood of Mattancherry in Kochi, Kerala. This palace holds significant historical and cultural importance, reflecting the colonial influences and architectural brilliance of the region.', 'Kerela', 'Active'),
(112, 'KRISHNAPURAM PALACE', 'admin/monument-upload/KRISHNAPURAM PALACE1.jpg', 'INR', '20', '250', 'Per Person', '6', 'Kayamkulam, Kerala', 'KRISHNAPURAM PALACE.php', 'Krishnapuram Palace, located in Kerala, is a magnificent historical palace that showcases the architectural grandeur and cultural heritage of the region. Built during the 18th century by the Travancore kingdom, this palace stands as a testament to the rich history and royal legacy of Kerala.</', 'Kerela', 'Active'),
(113, ' HILL PALACE MUSEUM', 'admin/monument-upload/ HILL PALACE MUSEUM1.jpg', 'INR', '20', '250', 'Per Person', '7', 'Ernakulam, Kerala', ' HILL PALACE MUSEUM.php', 'Hill Palace Museum, situated in Kerala, is a prestigious heritage museum that offers a captivating journey into the royal history and cultural heritage of the region. It is located on a picturesque hilltop, surrounded by lush greenery, creating a serene and enchanting atmosphere for visitors.</', 'Kerela', 'Active'),
(114, 'HILL PALACE MUSEUM', 'admin/monument-upload/HILL PALACE MUSEUM1.jpg', 'INR', '20', '250', 'Per Person', '7', 'Ernakulam, Kerala', 'HILL PALACE MUSEUM.php', 'Hill Palace Museum, situated in Kerala, is a prestigious heritage museum that offers a captivating journey into the royal history and cultural heritage of the region. It is located on a picturesque hilltop, surrounded by lush greenery, creating a serene and enchanting atmosphere for visitors', 'Kerela', 'Active'),
(115, 'THIRUVALLUVAR STATUE', 'admin/monument-upload/THIRUVALLUVAR STATUE1.jpg', 'INR', '20', '20', 'Per Person', '7', 'Valluvar Kottam Island Kanyakumari, Tamil Nadu', 'THIRUVALLUVAR STATUE.php', 'The Thiruvalluvar Statue is an iconic monument located on Valluvar Kottam Island in Kanyakumari, Tamil Nadu, India. It is a statue of the renowned Tamil poet and philosopher Thiruvalluvar and stands as a symbol of wisdom, knowledge, and cultural heritage in the region.', 'Tamil Nadu', 'Active'),
(116, 'VIVEKANANDA ROCK MEMORIAL', 'admin/monument-upload/VIVEKANANDA ROCK MEMORIAL1.jpg', 'INR', '20', '20', 'Per Person', '7', 'Kanyakumari, Tamil Nadu', 'VIVEKANANDA ROCK MEMORIAL.php', 'The Vivekananda Rock Memorial is a renowned monument situated on Vivekananda Rock in Kanyakumari, Tamil Nadu, India. It commemorates the visit of Swami Vivekananda, a revered spiritual leader, to the rock and serves as a symbol of his teachings and philosophies.', 'Tamil Nadu', 'Active'),
(117, 'VIVEKANANDA ROCK MEMORIAL', 'admin/monument-upload/VIVEKANANDA ROCK MEMORIAL1.jpg', 'INR', '20', '20', 'Per Person', '7', 'Kanyakumari, Tamil Nadu', 'VIVEKANANDA ROCK MEMORIAL.php', 'The Vivekananda Rock Memorial is a renowned monument situated on Vivekananda Rock in Kanyakumari, Tamil Nadu, India. It commemorates the visit of Swami Vivekananda, a revered spiritual leader, to the rock and serves as a symbol of his teachings and philosophies.', 'Tamil Nadu', 'Active'),
(118, 'PADMANABHAPURAM PALACE', 'admin/monument-upload/PADMANABHAPURAM PALACE1.jpg', 'INR', '35', '300', 'Per Person', '7', 'Kanyakumari, Tamil Nadu', 'PADMANABHAPURAM PALACE.php', 'Padmanabhapuram Palace, located in Padmanabhapuram, Tamil Nadu, India, is a well-preserved wooden palace showcasing exquisite architecture and cultural heritage. With intricate woodwork, stunning murals, and beautiful courtyards, it is a popular destination for tourists seeking to explore the rich history of the region.', 'Tamil Nadu', 'Active'),
(119, 'ALAMPARAI FORT', 'admin/monument-upload/ALAMPARAI FORT1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', '7', 'Villupuram, Tamil Nadu', 'ALAMPARAI FORT.php', 'The Alamparai Fort, located in Kadappakkam village near Marakkanam in Tamil Nadu, India, is a historic fortification. With a serene coastal setting, it offers a glimpse into the regions past. Though now in ruins, the fort remains a popular attraction, attracting visitors with its intriguing history and scenic surroundings.', 'Tamil Nadu', 'Active'),
(120, 'VELLORE FORT', 'admin/monument-upload/VELLORE FORT1.jpg', 'INR', '5', '5', 'Per Person', '7', 'Vellore, Tamil Nadu', 'VELLORE FORT.php', 'Vellore Fort is a historic stronghold located in Vellore, Tamil Nadu, India. Built during the 16th century, it is renowned for its architectural grandeur and rich historical significance. The fort showcases a unique blend of Dravidian, Islamic, and European architectural styles, making it a popular tourist attraction.', 'Tamil Nadu', 'Active'),
(121, 'TAJ MAHAL', 'admin/monument-upload/TAJ MAHAL1.jpg', 'INR', '50', '1200', 'Per Person', '7', 'Agra, Uttar Pradesh', 'TAJ MAHAL.php', 'Taj Mahal is a renowned mausoleum located in Agra, Uttar Pradesh, India. It is a symbol of love, built by Emperor Shah Jahan in memory of his wife, Mumtaz Mahal. The Taj Mahal is celebrated for its exquisite white marble architecture, intricate carvings, and beautiful gardens, attracting millions of visitors annually.', 'Tamil Nadu', 'Active'),
(122, 'TAJ MAHAL', 'admin/monument-upload/TAJ MAHAL1.jpg', 'INR', '50', '1200', 'Per Person', '7', 'Agra, Uttar Pradesh', 'TAJ MAHAL.php', 'Taj Mahal is a renowned mausoleum located in Agra, Uttar Pradesh, India. It is a symbol of love, built by Emperor Shah Jahan in memory of his wife, Mumtaz Mahal. The Taj Mahal is celebrated for its exquisite white marble architecture, intricate carvings, and beautiful gardens, attracting millions of visitors annually.', 'Tamil Nadu', 'Active'),
(123, 'TAJ MAHAL', 'admin/monument-upload/TAJ MAHAL1.jpg', 'INR', '50', '1200', 'Per Person', '7', 'Agra, Uttar Pradesh', 'TAJ MAHAL.php', 'Taj Mahal is a renowned mausoleum located in Agra, Uttar Pradesh, India. It is a symbol of love, built by Emperor Shah Jahan in memory of his wife, Mumtaz Mahal. The Taj Mahal is celebrated for its exquisite white marble architecture, intricate carvings, and beautiful gardens, attracting millions of visitors annually.', 'Uttar Pradesh', 'Active'),
(124, 'AGRA FORT', 'admin/monument-upload/AGRA FORT1.jpg', 'INR', '40', '550', 'Per Person', '7', 'Agra, Uttar Pradesh', 'AGRA FORT.php', 'Agra Fort, located in Agra, Uttar Pradesh, India, is a historic fortress that served as the main residence of the Mughal emperors. Constructed with red sandstone, the fort showcases exquisite architecture and houses palaces, mosques, and gardens, making it a popular tourist attraction.', 'Uttar Pradesh', 'Active'),
(125, 'FATEHPUR SIKRI FORT', 'admin/monument-upload/FATEHPUR SIKRI FORT1.jpg', 'INR', '35', '550', 'Per Person', '7', 'Fatehpur Sikri, Uttar Pradesh', 'FATEHPUR SIKRI FORT.php', 'Fatehpur Sikri Fort, located in Fatehpur Sikri, Uttar Pradesh, India, is a historical fort known for its magnificent architecture. Constructed during the Mughal era, the fort showcases a blend of Islamic and Hindu architectural styles. It is a UNESCO World Heritage site and attracts visitors with its grand courtyards, intricately carved structures, and rich cultural heritage.', 'Uttar Pradesh', 'Active'),
(126, 'KANS QILA', 'admin/monument-upload/KANS QILA1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', '7', 'Mathura, Uttar Pradesh', 'KANS QILA.php', 'Kans Qila is a historical fort located in Uttar Pradesh, India. It holds significance in Hindu mythology as the birthplace of Lord Krishna and is associated with various legends and stories. The fort is known for its architectural grandeur and attracts tourists and devotees from around the world.', 'Uttar Pradesh', 'Active'),
(127, 'AKBARS TOMB', 'admin/monument-upload/AKBARS TOMB1.jpg', 'INR', '20', '200', 'Per Person', '7', 'Agra, Uttar Pradesh', 'AKBARS TOMB.php', 'Akbars Tomb, located in Sikandra, Agra, Uttar Pradesh, is a magnificent mausoleum dedicated to Emperor Akbar, the great Mughal ruler. It showcases stunning Mughal architecture and is a significant historical site, attracting visitors from around the world to admire its grandeur and pay homage to the emperor.', 'Uttar Pradesh', 'Active'),
(128, 'METCALFE HALL', 'admin/monument-upload/METCALFE HALL1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', '7', 'Malda, West Bengal', 'METCALFE HALL.php', 'METCALFE HALL is a prominent heritage building in Kolkata, West Bengal, India. It was built in the 19th century and showcases a blend of classical Greek and Roman architectural styles. The hall serves as a cultural center and houses a library, exhibitions, and public events, attracting visitors interested in history and art.', 'West Bengal', 'Active'),
(129, 'EKLAKHI MAUSOLEUM', 'admin/monument-upload/EKLAKHI MAUSOLEUM1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', '7', 'Malda district, West Bengal', 'EKLAKHI MAUSOLEUM.php', 'Eklakhi Mausoleum, situated in Pandua, Malda district, West Bengal, India, is a historic monument of architectural significance. It is known for its unique octagonal shape and intricate terracotta ornamentation. The mausoleum reflects the rich cultural heritage of the region and attracts visitors interested in history and art.', 'West Bengal', 'Active'),
(130, 'HAZARDUARI PALACE', 'admin/monument-upload/HAZARDUARI PALACE1.jpg', 'INR', '20', '250', 'Per Person', '7', 'Murshidabad, West Bengal', 'HAZARDUARI PALACE.php', 'Hazarduari Palace, situated in Murshidabad, West Bengal, India, is a historic palace known for its magnificent architecture and grandeur. Built during the 19th century, it boasts of a thousand doors, though only 900 are functional. The palace now serves as a museum, showcasing artifacts from the era of Nawabs.', 'West Bengal', 'Active'),
(131, 'SAHID MINAR', 'admin/monument-upload/SAHID MINAR1.jpg', 'INR', '00', '00', 'Per Person', '7', 'Kolkata, West Bengal', 'SAHID MINAR.php', 'The Shaheed Minar, situated in Kolkata, West Bengal, India, is a historic monument commemorating the sacrifices of freedom fighters. Built in a fusion of architectural styles, it stands tall as a symbol of courage and patriotism. The monument is a popular landmark and a reminder of Indias struggle for independence.', 'West Bengal', 'Active'),
(132, 'ARCHAEOLOGICAL SITE MUSEUM', 'admin/monument-upload/ARCHAEOLOGICAL SITE MUSEUM1.jpg', 'INR', '5', '5', 'Per Person', '7', 'Tamluk, West Bengal', 'ARCHAEOLOGICAL SITE MUSEUM.php', 'The Archaeological Site Museum in West Bengal houses a collection of artifacts excavated from historical sites. It offers a glimpse into the regions rich cultural heritage, showcasing ancient relics, sculptures, and archaeological findings. Visitors can explore the exhibits to uncover the mysteries of the past and appreciate the artistry of bygone civilizations.', 'West Bengal', 'Active');
